Subject: Re:  No! Not periods anymore ;)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=iso-8859-1
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

On 04-Dec-97, Anton Reinauer wrote:
>On 03-Dec-97, Sami N=E4=E4t=E4nen wrote:
>>On 03-Dec-97, Wright J.A wrote:

>>>   Also, i want to write a 3d polygon space sim for 030+ machines...

>>Well the frontier most likely is using just the blitter. BUT it will
>>calculate new lines while the blitting is done. and after the blit is
>>finished an interrupt handler then writes next blit to the blitter.

>  Hmmmm, I'd be very interested in that! -and I'm sure many others would=

>too :-)

>>With this way you can draw a whole lot more polygons than using normal
>>blitting commands from blitz. Disavantage is that you have to write
>your
>>own blitting routines... And that can be pain in the a**!

>   You can have parallel blitting in Blitz, you just have to use
>interleaved bitmaps- I don't know if that helps with your polygon
>filling though :-/

Yes the last blitting in the command is runned simultaneously with the
code. But when you are drawing polygons, you first need to draw the lines=

and then fill it. After that you have to copy the filled polygon in the
desired pitplanes. This is the reason to that big slowness if you use
more than 4 bitplanes. Too much copying to do. :(


