 Hiya,

> I've got to agree with Dave here currently i'm  workin  on  a
> few  routines  in  blitz mode so won't be using any mui stuff
> for a while however I do keep all mail i recieve to this list
> currently  back  to  around  November 96 so any questions and
> answers that appear on this list may well come in helpful  at
> a later date.

Well inhave alreayd  awnserd  this  question  once,  but  the
awnser   must  have  sliped  past  you.  My  awnser  was  the
following.

I dont do this just to make people pissed of when  they  dont
receive  the awnser to a question that has been posted to the
list. The reason I dont awnser to the list is that the  mails
intend  to  get quite long, and is ALWAYS accompanied with an
example on how to do what the asked about. Now If I only  got
lets say a mail every week or so, then I whould have awnsered
to the list. But since they are a couple of mail  everyday  I
wont.  Some peopel on the list get pissed of when people send
source codes to the list, since it makes  teh  mails  bigger,
and  it  takes  longer  to grab them. Now my mails arn't that
huge (Some times up to 6-8Kb but only  sometimes),  but  they
are many, and that whould just be the same thing as if I send
one HUGE mail everyday. And I wont take the crapp  for  this.
Not when I can awnser directly without any hassels.

I'm thinking  of  letting  all  the  people  that  wants  all
questions  and  awnser  about  the MUI lib that I receive and
send, send me thier  e-mail  and  I  whould  add  them  to  a
MUIGroup  in  YAM, and post the awnsers and questions to that
Group, so all who told me they wanted it  will  recive  them.
I'm not quite sure about this yet, but if anyof you guys have
any comments about this then please  mail  me  directly  with
them.  No  need  to  do  this  if it's only 1 or 2 people who
whould be intrested in the idea.

> catch ya
> snoopy

Hmm I just have to ask ...Is it ^SnOoPy^ from #Amirc Dalnet?

 ByE,

