 Hiya,

> Now you may say "Well  if I send it to the
> list, everyone   will  see  the awnser and
> learn!", well  since  we  awnser  directly
> to you this  wont  happen, and  the people
> on the list will only see the question and
> not the awnsers.

> Hmm. well  I  thought  that  was the whole
> point of the  blitz list.If  someones  got
> problems  anyone  who knows can help them,
> But also everyone  else can see the answer
> as well  and  wont  need to  ask  the same
> thing  again. (hopefully) Surely  you  get
> lots  of  questions   the  same, which  if
> answered  on the list might  not happen as
> much.

Well Dave, don't  think  I  dont  awnser the
questions directly to the mailing list, just
because I think it's fun to bug the hell out
of everyone, when they dont  get the awnser.

The reason  I  dont  do  it  is  because the
questions  I  get  isn't  the kind where you
simple can awnser YES  or  NO. The questions
I get are mainly  HOW  questions, and belive
me, people   attempts   to  write  the  most
advanced MUI  applications as  the first MUI
application   they    write. The   questions
need  a  long explination  on  what tags etc
to  use, and  which  tags  not  to  use. And
many  awnsers  it  accompanied  with a peice
of source  code, to  illustrate what I mean,
and how do do what they asked.

And I have seen  people that has sent source
codes along with  their mails, getting  very
unfriendly awnsers from people beeing pissed
of when  they  keep  getting  bombarded with
source codes, since they make the mails much
larger, and it will take.

It's not that the source codes are that big,
but since they are  many it will  almost be
the same thing.

So to make things much easyer for all of us,
please mail us directly.

Thanks, from the people as Vivid Imagination =

longer to get them from the mail server.

 ByE,

-- =

