Message-Id: <E0xdvPv-0007Hz-00@mserv1a.u-net.net>

On  4 Dec 97 at 21:21, Steven Pearson spewed forth:

> I need to get some accurate timings from a loop of code.
> 
> I don't mind being in blitz mode if it will improve accuracy. And banging the
> hardware is fine too.
> 
> I can only get time down to a 50th of a second (1 frame) and this doesn't seem
> to be accurate enough.

 If its possible, you could run your loop a silly amount of times, 
say 10000 and time how long it takes for that. Then divide the 
resultant time by 10000 to get the time for one loop, like this:

#NUMLOOPS = 10000
BLITZ
ResetTimer
For i.w = 1 to #NUMLOOPS
; Your loop goes in here
Next i
looptime.f = Ticks; accurate to 50ths, you could also use Timer
oneloop.f = looptime / #NUMLOOPS
AMIGA
NPrint oneloop; Print to CLI window
ClickMouse
End

Farewell, for now,

.oO David McMinn Oo.
-=-=-=-=-==-=-=-=-=-
*A1200T 1.3Gb 16xCD*
-=-=-=-=-==-=-=-=-=-


