On 27-Dec-97, jaraiza@geocities.com wrote:

>I've searched Aminet and other sources for a cheap and efficient mode to=

>connect my A1200 and a PC, but EasyLink (Parallel) is shareware and
>crap. On the other side, EasyTransfer (Even 2.0) isn't that bad, and is
>freeware, but it's still outdated.

I believe I've heard of a bunch of other ones that are freeware and still=

more of that type of program that are shareware and commercial.  I
suppose the correct Amiga-user thing to do would be to support the
people who have already developed such programs (I'm sure that they're
superb) but I know what it's like to not want to spend cash =3D)

>Another good idea, would be code a proxie-like conection to access INet
>with both machines at one phoneline, but that would require an Ethernet
>like connection...

I know this has been done on the Mac and PC, I don't know why it
wouldn't be possible on the Amiga.  You'll have to have a special
router coded on the PC, which may be quite a pain to code.

I know that when I dialup my PPP account using my Amiga I always
get better CPS & overall speed than when I logon using my 486DX2/66...

-- =


