Mime-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: TEXT/PLAIN; CHARSET=US-ASCII


On Mon, 1 Dec 1997 16:12:20 GMT Mike Carter 
<57229007%mmu.ac.uk@uk.ac.essex.mailhost> wrote:

> How do you pass an array into a procedure?  Do I have to use 
> pointers?

yes
Use following method to pass arrays/newtypes...


Newtype .mytype
	parameter1
	paremeter2
....
end newtype



Statement bleurgh{the_object_address.l}
deftype .mytype *something
*something=the_address.l
*something\parameter1=100
end statement


deftype .mytype myobject

myobject\parameter1=1231
bleurgh{&myobject}
nprint myobject\parameter1

-----
for an array, replace &myobject with &myarray(0)
and use Peek/Poke (or assembly) to manipulate the array.

(I suggest you use asm)




Christos Dimitrakakis (aka Olethros)
Electronic Engineer,
Software Developer for the Amiga computer
University of Essex




@ENDNODE
