Andrew Ballard wrote:
> 
> Is it possible to blit to a bitmap area that is actualy outside the
> bitmap?
> 
> Let me explain.  Im trying a new scrolling method that will
> continuously hardware scroll.  Because when the edge of a bitmap is
> reached, it actualy wraps around, but one pixel up.  If I just blit
> my background shapes one pixel down when this is reached you should
> have continuous hardware scroll (Its probably very system
> un-friendly, though!!! (sorry guys)).
> 

To blit off of the bitmap you must have created your bitmap using
CludgeBitmap within a previously allocated area of memory, otherwise you
will be writing over memory that doesn`t belong to you and will
eventually crash the machine.

I have done various methods of scrolling bitmaps in the past and have a
working example of the horizontal wrap technique you are describing if
you would like it.

See you,

Liz.                     tucks@pavilion.co.uk
  
