Hi,

actually I=B4ve gotten around this by using a slightly different method 
which uses more chipram but still is very memory efficent. It works 
by waitning until the display has scrolled one block and then changes 
the pointers to the bitplanes so that the bitmap "jumps". If anyone 
wants the source they can mail me. This is also the method Liz is 
describing  (I think).

