On 10-Dec-97, &%!@#%%^&!! wrote:


>I have got it working now and this shows you can blit off of the 
>bitmap.  Thanks for the help and I had thought about it running off 
>into memory, I have made the bitmap higher to cater for this.

>Although you can blit off the bitmap, my debugger sees it as an 
>error.  Its fine when I turn the debugger off except that now simple 
>progression bugs that the debugger would normaly alert me to crash
>the computer.

>Is there anyway of just disabling the "Out of Bitmap" error and 
>non-other?

>Any help appreciated.

Yes!  Put the command 

RunErrsOff

Before the blitting code and

RunErrsOn

after it.   This tells the debugger to skip checking this part of the code.

Just remember to remove them when you make the finished version.

                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
