On Tue, 9 Dec 1997, Tim Johnson wrote:

> I just upgraded my machine to OS3.1.  I haven't had any problems,
> except now Blitz doesn't work.  What's the deal?  It gets a GURU
> 8000 000B or 8100 000B.  I don't have the BSS.

I've all kinds of such problems with Blitz, and most of them started when 
I upgraded to 3.1 -- I eventually got Blitz working reliably again, by 
rebuilding my deflibs file, (and removing and documents from the 
blitzlibs directory!) and I now run Blitz from a shell, which is a 
holdover from before I rebuilt deflibs.  It may or may not run from 
Workbench now.  

> On a sidenote, I bought my rom from Paxtron Corp.  It came packaged in
> a box inside the Paxtron box.  This box said it was from Black Forest
> Products GmbH, the people who make the JetFire.  Anyway, after I took
> the 3.1 rom out of the box, I looked at it, and it said this:
> 
> Kickstart 3.1 (V40.63)
>     Amigo 2000
>  (c) 1984, 1993 Connodore Corp.

Wow, that's odd.  I got my ROM in a box from Black Forest as well, but I 
didn't notice any typos on the ROM.  

