Subject: BLITZ Mode
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=us-ascii
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Hi
  I seem to have a problem with blitz mode. I don`t use it much
  anymore since I read what the RKMs said about hardware hacks.
  But I have an old program I have recently been trying to get
  working. It worked fine until I tried to create an executble
  then I had problems with memory allocation although I think that
  is sorted now. I also seem to have a problem with BLITZ - AMIGA
  modes , I go into BLITZ mode and it works fine but then I go back
  into AMIGA mode at the end of the program to display any error
  messages. At this point just after this command I get crashes, not
  every time but if I run my program about three times on the last
  time when I return to the workbench screen it is screwed up, it
  looks like its been split in half and the halves are the wrong way
  round.
   If I remove all commands after `AMIGA` apart from `End` and
   I don`t seem to have any problems from the display, away I do
  still have another problem.
  This game is two player and when I plug a joystick in the mouse
  port I use fire button to do moves in the game, the problem is
  these fire button presses seem to be queued and so when I go back
  to workbench the game is run again before I get chance to move
  the mouse pointer away from my program icon. 
  As I said I`m in BLITZ mode until the very last bit, how are these
  presses getting queued in BLITZ mode ?  and I can`t do anything like
  Flushevents because I get crashed like I wrote about above. 

  All a bit strange to me it seems like `BLITZ` isn`t shutting
  down the system properly and then `AMIGA` gets confused, but
  I`m probably wrong.

BTW: The RWEDebugger does not find any problems, I only notice a
     problem when I make an exe.

Thanks for any help

DAVE


@ENDNODE
