From: BootBlock of Carnage <bootblock@geocities.com>
Reply-To: bootblock@geocities.com
To: Blitz List <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Tue, 30 Dec 1997 01:36:18 GMT0
Message-ID: <yam7303.904.3326864@mail.geocities.com>
X-Mailer: YAM 1.3.5 [020] - Amiga Mailer by Marcel Beck
Organization: Private UK Amiga Geezer!
Subject: Blitzy things ...
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain


One of the main problems with Blitz, is the size of the overall executable.
The (obvious?) reason for that is if you used one command from a library, the
WHOLE library would be included.

This is just an idea ....

Couldn't there be a "Included Libraries" prefs window in Blitz that you could
modify when you create your executable. So, if you just use one command from a
library, Blitz will
_only_ include that command's code and discard the rest of the library
(depending on wether you disabled the commands' library code)?

If you used a command that requires the code from another command in that
library, there could be a list of commands in a listview, and the ones that
require another command's code will not be allowed to be "turned off", for
obvious reasons.

Does that make any sense to anyone?

Blitz really needs to offer more control over the final executable.

-- 
| A1200/28Mhz/2+4Mb/K56Flex/HyperCOM | Amiga Blitz 2 coder type UK bloke! |
