  ---Original Message-----
From: BootBlock of Carnage <bootblock@geocities.com>

Hi,


>One of the main problems with Blitz, is the size of the overall =
executable.
>The (obvious?) reason for that is if you used one command from a =
library, the
>WHOLE library would be included.
>
>This is just an idea ....
>
>Couldn't there be a "Included Libraries" prefs window in Blitz that you =
could
>modify when you create your executable. So, if you just use one command =
from a
>library, Blitz will
>_only_ include that command's code and discard the rest of the library
>(depending on wether you disabled the commands' library code)?

<Snip>

>Does that make any sense to anyone?

It's a good idea in theory, but in practice it won't work.  How do you =
know which code you can discard?  There is no easy way Blitz will know =
which code is used by each command.

Even if there was some arcane way to do it, the time would we better =
spent coming up with a different library system.  A different library =
system also could get rid of the library numbers (solving a lot of =
hassle), and you would be able to have more than 256 libraries on one =
system.

Ciao,
Julian Kinraid




@ENDNODE
