Hi Mike,

> After getting my nice new 1260 last week I was a little peeved at the 
> amount of software which doesn't work and/or corrupts graphics - 
> sometimes even no sound !?!  Anyway one good way to fix all this is 
> by turning the caches off.  Is it possible to do this through one of 
> the OS libraries.  I know you could call a DOS command such as "C:CPU 
> NOCACHES" or something but I want to do it from within a program.

Turn the cache off on your 060 and you might as well be using
an 030. When I use the nocache option on my 040 it takes me back
to the time I was using an 020. If you want this sort of thing
in your own programs then you're better off trying to flush the
cache using the commands that were discussed on here recently.
What problems have you had that makes you want to turn the cache
off in your own program?

Cheers,

Paul

