X-Mailer: Simeon for Win32 Version 4.1.2 Build (32)
X-Authentication: IMSP
Mime-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: TEXT/PLAIN; CHARSET=US-ASCII

For Programs working on 030 and not on 060, you'd be better off trying 
to disable copyback cache only, since this is the most likely cause of 
problems.

As for your own program, try and have a look at the NDK to see what 
things you should be avoiding when using a 68060. Writing to/Reading 
from chip ram and/or custom chip registers is a bit different than 
using fastram, since:
Not only the CPU can access chip ram.
Custom chip registers can either be written to or read from and are 
triggered each time you write/read them. This can cause problems with 
particular types of cache. Similar problems exist with Zorro boards; 
These problems are documented in the NDK...


Christos Dimitrakakis (aka Olethros)
Electronic Engineer,
Software Developer for the Amiga computer
University of Essex




@ENDNODE
