Message-Id: <SIMEON.9712092132.A@fpgapc13.essex.ac.uk>
Date: Tue, 9 Dec 1997 21:42:32 +0000 (GMT)
Priority: NORMAL
X-Mailer: Simeon for Win32 Version 4.1.2 Build (32)
X-Authentication: IMSP
Mime-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: TEXT/PLAIN; CHARSET=US-ASCII

Oh, btw, I just found out that chip ram and custom register area are 
supposed to be marked by the MMU so that copyback cache is not used 
there.. 
This probably only occurs when you do a full boot, (setpatch may do 
that), so only floppy-booting games should be affected - but I don't 
know much about this really, so I'll just shut up.




Christos Dimitrakakis (aka Olethros)
Electronic Engineer,
Software Developer for the Amiga computer
University of Essex




@ENDNODE
