On 31-Dec-97, BootBlock of Carnage wrote:

> >Why doing it like that? There are command "wtitle" which can change
> >both of them. If I remember correctly this is part of Original Blitz o=
r
> >from some BUM.

> Use SetWindowTitles_ instead, because WTitle nukes 200 bytes of memory
> everytime you call it. .....

>   WindowTitle$   =3D "Hello, this is your winda!"
>   ScreenTitle$   =3D "What a nice screen!"

>    SetWindowTitles_ Peek.l(Addr Window(0)),&WindowTitle$,&ScreenTitle$

This will copy those strings to memory and I think it will free the memor=
y
as well. If not then it is even worse that wtitle.

Oh! and that wtitle will free the memory what it uses after the program
exits.


