Subject: Re: Checking extra serial devices.
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

On 10-Dec-97, Budda/Progress tapped "Re: Checking extra serial devices."
on his keyboard:
>> 
>>  Hello,
>> 
>> I have a small problem, that I cant seem to
>> figure out how to solve. I have a MULTIFACE
>> 3 serial card in my A4000, and I want to
>> check when data is beeing sent and received
>> on the serial port on the card.
>> 
>> If I where using  the  normal  serial port,
>> then I  know  I chould  bit test  the right
>> adresses  (dont have them in my head, but I
>> do have them), to  check  wheter the serial
>> port was receiving or sending data, but how
>> do I do this on my MULTIFACE 3 serial card?
>> 
>> The serial card uses a device  called duart
>> device, and  I  think  it  runs on  unit 1.
>> 
>> Does anyone  have a  clue  how  to do this?
>> Some source whould be great. What I want to
>> do is make a  small  program  that layes on
>> my WB, or what ever  screen I want, and has
>> to lights that blink when  the  serial port
>> recives or sends data. I  know  that  there
>> are program to do this, but I want to write
>> my own. I'm  using  the new MUI lib that we
>> have  developed  for teh GUI, so I can make
>> it the way I want it.
>> 
>If you load the serial device then this will lock the serial port for 
>your programs access only which would result in no other program 
>being able to send data.  In turn this would defeat the purpose of 
>the program?

Not true, what you could do is set it to "shared", this will mean that
any program that does not need exclusive use of the serial port, will be
able to work simutainiously.  Unfortunatly, this can mean that if you
use "ReadSerialString" in your main loop, other programs will miss
sections.  If I run my PDial program (checks for incoming calls be
checking for a "RING" every second, Miami misses some important bits
during login like "CONNECT" and "Password:".

/Rick/
-- 
=====================================================
Rick Hodger - Comms Programmer for #Desktop Corruption#
