On Wed, 17 Dec 1997 20:35:30 -0500 Allan Pedersen=20
<cfist%post8.tele.dk@uk.ac.essex.mailhost> wrote:

> Somebody wrote something about wanting to be able to "hide" some text in =
the
> .exe file!! This is text like: "L:MyProg.key". In my player i use Chr$(nu=
m) to
> hide text like this!!
>=20
> Ex:
> instead of:
> of=3DOpenFile(1,"S:MyProg.prefs")=20
>=20
> i have:
> file$=3DChr$(83)+Chr$(58)+Chr$(77)+Chr$(121)+Chr$(80)+Chr$(114)+Chr$(101)=
+Chr$(102)+Chr$(115)
> of=3DOpenFile(1,file$)=20
>=20

> I know this is a =A4#"=A4% long way of doing it!! But i think it's safe!!=
 And u
> can't edit the .exe file :o)
>
This is not safe at all ;
the chr$()+... willbe calculated and placed as a constant somewhere in=20
your executable.


And you CAN edit the .exe file with a hex editor, or even Ced:)


A slightly safer way is to do the following, to ensure that your string=20
is dynamically alocated

txt:
data$"a","b","c".. (scrambled character set)
string:
data 32,12,13....  (numbers representing places in the array)

restore txt
for n=3D....
  cset$(n)=3Dread x$
next n
restore string
for n=3D..
   f$+cset$(n)
next n

you could also scramble it using an encryption algorithm..
but STILL

a utility like SnoopDos will easily figure out which file you`re trying=20
to load..=20





Christos Dimitrakakis (aka Olethros)
Electronic Engineer,
Software Developer for the Amiga computer
University of Essex
http://esewww.essex.ac.uk/~cdimita



@ENDNODE
