>A slightly safer way is to do the following, to ensure that your string

>is dynamically alocated

>txt:
>data$"a","b","c".. (scrambled character set)
>string:
>data 32,12,13....  (numbers representing places in the array)

>restore txt
>for n=....
>  cset$(n)=read x$
>next n
>restore string
>for n=..
>   f$+cset$(n)
>next n

>you could also scramble it using an encryption algorithm..
>but STILL

>a utility like SnoopDos will easily figure out which file you`re trying

>to load.. 

