Message-ID: <yam7292.1261.3287984@mail.sci.fi>
X-Mailer: YAM 1.3.4 [020] - Amiga Mailer by Marcel Beck
Organization: Universal Abductions Inc
Subject: Ciphering
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

Here is a solution for ciphering strings so changing them in exe is a bit
harder...  The program asks for string variable names, their contents and
writes a file with the encoded variables in ram:  That file should be
included in your program source.  To use the encoded strings in your program
you need to include the function decode and process the encoded strings with
it.

;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
Function.s decode{s$}
  d=0
  r$=""
  For i.w=1 To Len(s$)
    c$=Mid$(s$,i,1)
    If c$>="A"
      r$=r$+Chr$(Asc(c$)-d)
    Else
      r$=r$+c$
      EndIf
    d=(d+1) MOD 5
    Next
Function Return r$
End Function

If WriteFile(1,"ram:encoded.vars")
  Repeat
    DefaultOutput
    Print "Enter string variable name (empty quits):"
    v$=Edit$(25)
    If v$<>""
      Print "Enter string:"
      s$=Edit$(1024)
      d=0
      r$=""
      For i.w=1 To Len(s$)
        c$=Mid$(s$,i,1)
        If c$>="A"
          r$=r$+Chr$(Asc(c$)+d)
        Else
          r$=r$+c$
          EndIf
        d=(d+1) MOD 5
        Next
      NPrint v$,"="+Chr$(34),r$,Chr$(34)
      NPrint "Decoded:",decode{r$}
      FileOutput 1
      NPrint v$,"="+Chr$(34),r$,Chr$(34)
      EndIf
    Until v$=""
    NPrint "Results are in ram:encoded.vars"
  EndIf
End
;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
-- 
- Kaitsu -



@ENDNODE
