   I`ve written a simple clear bitmap routine in Asm... and on my 060 it
is about 76% faster than the Cls command.. BUT, i have no idea how fast
it would be on slower machines.. eg 030`s .... because i figure that for
slower machines Cls would be faster as the blitter would be faster than
there cpu...  so on what cpu does it become faster to use my cpu asm
routine rather than the Cls????

Note: all my asm routine does, is to MOVE.l #0,-(a0) from the end of the
bitplanes to the beginning....


