Hi James,

> I can't find a way to do this, I've come close in that I can write the
> code in an editor and use a program to assenble it, but the problem is
> that I need to be able to pass the location of some data in memory to
> the code section I'm executing.
> 
> I tried using GetReg and MOVE to store the address in one of the address
> registers (a0) but when I use Call to run the code, all of the registers
> get bent out of shape and I lose the address.

I was playing around with bitmaps a while back, creating them in one
program
and using another program to write to the same bitmap. To do this I
passed
the addresses I needed as program parameters when the second program
started.
I forget the syntax off-hand but on the lines of 
Execute ("second_proggie",address,address, etc.). Then the addresses can
be found by the second program by checking the passed parameters.

There is probably a 'proper' way to do this but it worked for me and I
can't see any way it would trash the system as long as you were sure
that the addresses you pass are correct.

See you,

Liz.                     tucks@pavilion.co.uk
  
