On Wed, 17 Dec 1997 12:32:04 -0500 Garfield Benjamin 
<gbenjam%sosbbs.com@uk.ac.essex.mailhost> wrote:

> 
> 
>    It will work fine... this is your basic RLE (Run Length Encoding)
>    compression. You've seen the results of this compression every
>    time you save/load an IFF picture file...
> 
Yup, and it is usually followed by some other coding (huffman,lz (ie 
lha), arithmetic..)
In principle, using one of those directly will produce the same amount 
of compression, without using any run-length coding, but in practice, 
runlength coding changes the file into a form that is much easier (ie 
faster) for a 'proper' compression algorithm to compress.


