Hi,=20

>   I've found that, if I change the name of the blitz lib =
'ColorWhell.gadget1'
>to 'ColorWhell.library1', two
>new commands are available : #ConvertRGBToHSB_(rgb,hsb)# and
>#ConvertHSBToRGB_(hsb,rgb)# .

<snip>

>   But how can I use these two commands in my prog ?
>   All I've try finish with a bad crash :-(

It's a bug in FDConvert (and your ColorWheel.library1 file).  I can give =
you my fixed version of FDConvert, but you will need the =
colorwheel_lib.fd file.  If you don't have that, tell me what lib number =
your colorwheel.library1 uses, and I'll make one for you.

>   Perhaps, it's not the good way for convert a RGB value to HSB...

It's a good way IMHO.  If you're doing it for you're image processor, =
you might want to make your own conversion process.  You could also make =
ones for converting=20
RGB to HSL (luminance) and things like that.  I've got some pseudo code =
for a number of routines if you want it.

Ciao,
Julian Kinraid




@ENDNODE
