How do I find out the x and y values inside a bitmap that is scrolling over an
IFF? That probably wasn't very clear so here's what I am doing; I have a beat
'em up game that uses a 640x200 bitmap that is scrolling around on a 1280x200
IFF. My problem is that I can't tell when the character is at the edge of the
bitmap so I can scroll the IFF. Make sense?
