Content-Type: text/plain; charset=us-ascii
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Jake Frederick wrote:

> My problem is that I can't tell when the character is at the edge
> of the
> bitmap so I can scroll the IFF. Make sense?

If you are displaying the bitmap using the DisplayBitmap command then
you will know the top lefthand coordinates of the displayed area.
Therefore you can subtract this from the coordinates of your character
which will leave the you with the distance that your character is from
the edge of the displayed area.

eg. if you were displaying the bitmap at an x coordinate of 50 and your
character was being displayed at an x coordinate of 80 then he must be
30 pixels away from the lefthand edge of the displayed area.


See you,

Liz.                     tucks@pavilion.co.uk
  
