 On   Fri, 20 Jan 1978 13:24:50 +0500
 someone wrote
 
> How do I find out the x and y values inside a bitmap that is 
>scrolling over an
 > IFF? That probably wasn't very clear so here's what I am doing; I 
>have a beat
 > 'em up game that uses a 640x200 bitmap that is scrolling around on 
>a 1280x200
 > IFF. My problem is that I can't tell when the character is at the 
>edge of the
>  bitmap so I can scroll the IFF. Make sense?
 
 
 Sorry if anyone else has answered this, but heres how I`d do it..
 
 scrollx=0: scrolly=0  Position of the screen
 x=0:y=0  The coords of the shape
 
 repeat
 	displaybitmap 0,scrollx,scrolly
 	x+joyx(0)
 	y+joyy(0)
 	if x>160 then scrollx+1
 	if x<160 then scrollx-1
 until something
 
 Basically, you just test to see if the character is at the middle of 
 the screen, then change the position of the bitmap
 
 If youre using shapes use blit 0,x,y
 however if using sprites use
 displaysprite 0,x-scrollx,y-scrolly,0
 This will stop the sprites moving when the screen moves
 
 Regards
 Steven
  
 

-----------------------------------------------------
Steven Croy <AP6013.qmw.ac.uk> 

To avoid looking at a fool
            Smash your mirror

---------------------------------------------------------


@ENDNODE
