On 16 Dec 97 at 8:51, Krzysiek Jonko spewed forth:

> I've a little problem with "About" function with my program. When I
> compile program all texts are visible for each hacker, so making "new"
> version is quite easy...
> Is any easy way to get UNCRYPTED texts in program and CRYPTED in executable
> file? I've tried Cipher$ (or something like that) but this is very
> unfriendly function.

 You could try having all your texts as coded, i.e. instead of 
text$="hello" use text$="ifmmp" then in your program, before you need 
to use them, have a loop that goes through all your texts and change 
them i.e.
For i.w = 1 to len(text$)
  mid$(text$,1,i)=chr$(asc(mid$(text$,1,i))-1)
next i

 The easiest way to do this is have all your texts in an array, i.e. 
instead of text$ use text$(1) then you can use two nested for loops.


Farewell, for now,

.oO David McMinn Oo.
