Content-Type: text/plain

Hi,

>On 16 Dec, Krzysiek Jonko wrote:

>> I've a little problem with "About" function with my program. When I
>> compile program all texts are visible for each hacker, so making "new"
>> version is quite easy...
>> Is any easy way to get UNCRYPTED texts in program and CRYPTED in executable
>> file? I've tried Cipher$ (or something like that) but this is very
>> unfriendly function.

Here is an example which does it a little different.  The text itself is not
hidden (at least, in the hex editor it appears to be not hidden) - but there
is hidden in the code a routine which checks your text for alterations.

So, the hacker clearly sees your text in his hex editor, and alters it,
thinking he is very smart.  But now when he runs the program, the joke is on
him - he is caught, and the program refuses to run!  I even have included an
option to make the program crash after the requestor is seen, if you want to
really aggravate the hacker and make altered versions unusable.

This works by comparing your clearly visible text to parts of your other
clearly visible texts.  Also, even if he manages to figure out what you did,
and finds and alters all the other texts to go with his new message, now all
the other texts are messed up, and users will see that the program was
altered.

                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com

--BOUNDARY.7291.899.3727088.2
Content-Type: text/plain; name="About.test.bb"

WBStartup
WBenchToFront_
WbToScreen 0
Window 0,0,0,1,1,0,"",0,0  ;for the requestor
CatchDosErrs               ;also for the requestor
check$="Program by ME!"    ;this will show in hex editor
about$=Left$(check$,1)        ;gets "P"
a$="Here is some other stuff"
about$=about$+Mid$(a$,18,1)   ;now we have "Pr"
b$="These strings will all show"
e$="free ram ="
c$="Clearly in a hex editor too"
about$=about$+Right$(c$,1)            ;"Pro
d$="but it does the hacker no good."
about$=about$+Mid$(d$,27,1)           ;"Prog"
VWait 10                    ;just some filler
about$=about$+Mid$(e$,6,4)            ;"Program "
f$="NOT ENOUGH MEMORY!"
a=ExecVersion          ;just some other stuff
about$=about$+Mid$(d$,1,1)+Mid$(c$,7,2)  ;"Program by "
If Exists("Fonts:topaz.font")         ;more filler
  a=True
Else
  a=False
EndIf
about$=about$+Mid$(f$,12,2)+Right$(f$,1)  ;"Program by ME!

If check$=about$
   Request "About",check$,"OK"
Else
   Request "Warning","This program has been hacked!","OK"
   ;a=10/0          ;cause a crash!
EndIf
End


--BOUNDARY.7291.899.3727088.2--




@ENDNODE
