Hello Alvaro Thompson, on 25-Dec-97 20:48:10, you said,

 AT> I need to know the definition of the CTRL-C signal......... I got this of
 AT> someone....
 AT> SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C = 1<<12.

I Use

#SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C=1 ASL 12

and this line to detect the CTRL-C whenever I feel like it

Boolean.b = SetSignal_(0,#SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C) & #SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C

Or you could use Signal

Amiga make's it possible
