On 26-Dec-97, Steven Pearson wrote:
> Hello Alvaro Thompson, on 25-Dec-97 20:48:10, you said,

>  AT> I need to know the definition of the CTRL-C signal......... I got =
this
of
>  AT> someone....
>  AT> SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C =3D 1<<12.

> I Use

> #SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C=3D1 ASL 12

> and this line to detect the CTRL-C whenever I feel like it

> Boolean.b =3D SetSignal_(0,#SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C) & #SIGBREAKF_CTRL_C

Yes you can use this BUT IT CAN NOT BE CALLED FROM INTERRUPTS!!!!!
And setsignal belongs to commands that should be avoided
signals.l=3DChecksignal_(#signalmask) this is much more recommendable.
and give you possibility to check all the signals at the same time.

> Or you could use Signal

??? You mean sending the break to task. (This one can be called from INTs=
)

If you want you can wait breaksignal using wait_

