Hi Chris,

On 02-Dec-97, Chris Jonko wrote:
>Hi!
>I've a problem with datatypes lately. I would like to include a little
>statement to support datatypes on Kickstart 3.0 machines. I want to
>disable this statement for 2.0 users but when I include datatypes
>instruction to the main program, EXE file always want to open locale.library
>at startup - even on Kickstart 2.0 (it can't start!). Is possible to run
>program like that on 2.0 or I have to make two different programs for
>2.0 and 3.0 users?

Try like this:

If ExecVersion =>39    ;workbench is 3.xx or >
  (do datatype & locale stuff)
Else                   ;workbench 1.xx or 2.xx
  (do something else)
EndIf
-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



