On Thu, 11 Dec 1997, Peter Thor wrote:

> Ive been trying to set up a dualpf display for a while now but havent succeded.
> 
> I'm gonna use 2 16clrs/bitmaps, 8 bitmplanes, dualpf, fetchmode3 and agacolors required for dualpfmode.
> 
> The problem is that i want to use two different coloured bitmaps in a dualpffashion.
> But i dont know really how to make it happen. *must* they have the same palette (16clrs)??
> --
> --

If i'm not wrong, foreground screen (and so foreground bitmap) uses
colors from 0 to 15, while colours from 16 to 31 are used by your
background bitmap. If right, your palette must be a 32 colors palette!
Remember that color 0 is used as transparent color.
 
