MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

> InitCopList 0,44,256,$10028,8,32,8   ;agapal, dualpf, 8bpls, 32
>                                                 ;or should i set the
colourflag as 
>                                                   ;256 instead of 32?   

 Use:

 InitCopList 0,44,256,$10028,8,256,0

 And the SECRET is that the entire AGA chipset is a bit of a cludge, 
 having to remain compatible with the OCS/ECS Chipsets, so you 
 need to tell it to remap the Dual-Playfield colours to the higher
 colour-registers like this:

 DisplayControls 0,0,$1c00,$00ee

 Just add that line right after your InitCopList statement...



> What is wrong, am i stupid or what is going on here??

   No, you're not stupid it's just the AGA chipset must be told to remap
   the colour-registers otherwise it maps the colours for the OCS
   DualPlayfield-mode...


   I can throw together a simple source-demo... if you want just let me
   know and I'll e-mail it to you direct.


      Take  care,   
      GARFIELD
      _________________________
      Current projects...
      SideShooter(AMOS): 98% Complete
      Website(http://www.sosbbs.com/~gbenjam): 25% Complete



@ENDNODE
