 Hello,

> Surely you would use MUIAddObjHGroup()/MUIAddObjVGroup()
> to call a group? Isn't it the whole point of the new MUI
> lib? that you don't have to call  MUINewObject so often?
> Mmmm.......

Yes, albiro is  right (Good on ya m8), you  shouldn't  use
the Group-Mui object direclty, thats the whole idea behind
the new lib. When we developed the new  mui lib, we wanted
to give all those things  understandebal commands instead.
In  this  case   you   should   use   MUIAddObjVgroup  and
MUIAddObjHgroup. And   then    use    MUICreateVgroup  and =

MUICreateHgroup, to create them. And  to  set tags  to the
group  objects  you  should  use  MUIAddTags  (eg. set the
spacing etc.). You   should   only   need   to   use   the
MUINewObject when you want to make an unsupported  object,
like Text.Mui and Balancing.mui (Although I  think we will
add these as commands soon), and for custom classes (Which
I will tell you more on how to use these  sometime  in the
near futur. No need to e-mail us about this, since  we are
writing some examples for the mui lib, which will show how
to do basic and advanced things). =


*If ne1 have any questions  regarding the mui  lib  or it's*
*usage, then please e-mail use  directly,  since  people on*
*the groupk hasn't had the time  to get  into everything in*
*the lib yet, but we wrote it so we should have the awnsers*
*to your questions (I hope :)*

 ByE


-- =

