On 29-Dec-97 19:45:07, Tim Johnson wrote...

 TJ> When I run "Enforcer on", it comes up and says it's on the job.  If
 TJ> there is an Enforcer hit, the Power LED flickers, but Enforcer
 TJ> doesn't output any information on the hit.  What the heck?

Hmmm, I don't have an "Enforcer On" icon - which I assume you are refering
to when you Enforcer, instead I have - "Enforcer", "Enforcer Parallel",
"Enforcer Remote" and "Enforcer Local". I /think/ Enforcer normally sends
output to the serial port (someone may correct me on this). "Enforcer
Parallel", you guessed it to the parallel port. "Enforcer Remote" I don't
know, but the one I think you want is "Enforcer Local" which outputs hits
directly to a CON: window.

Perhaps you either have "Enforcer Local" missing or an older version, I got
this one off Aminet if I remember correctly.

Hope this helps. :)


--

