Do you know what is causing the Enforcer hit?  Some old libraries might =
not get fixed, so they might still cause Enforcer this.  You can write =
Blitz programs that don't cause enforcer hits, but sometimes you might =
have to single step through a program with the debugger to find where a =
hit is occurring.

>Do Acid Software still actually support Blitz anymore, or is it left to =
RWE?

I think Acid Software stopped developing Blitz a while ago, so now RWE =
have taken.  This is probably the reason why we haven't seen any changes =
to the main Blitz executable, because the source code was written by =
someone at Acid, and RWE find it a bit hard to understand.  Though RWE =
have been strangely quiet for a long time...

Ciao,
Julian Kinraid




