Hi Curt,

> I had Enforcer on my A2500, and also found that if you compile your exec
with
> the de-bugger on you will sometimes get enforcer hits.

I rarely use Enforcer because the Debugger was always causing hits which made
development time hell! To remove Enforcer hits with Blitz programs you have to
do a lot of tweaking and editing and it tends to be trial and error to remove
most
of the problems. When the debugger itself causes hits you can understand why
it's not an easy job to do.

> Also, a really odd one - I got Enforcer hits every time a particular note in
a
> particular med module was played in my Blitz program!  But never with any
> other med modules.  And not if I played the same module with medplayer
instead
> of Blitz.

Well that must be a problem with the lib itself unless the module contains
some
illegal features that break the MED rules IYSWIM. It's a bit like supporting
the
standards but not supporting the frequently used non-standards. For example,
can you imagine a web browser that doesn't support <center>? It's not part
of the html standard but it's very often used so all browsers support it.
After
saying that it's more likely that the player is dodgy :)

Cheers,

Paul

