Received: from roc-il2-16.ix.netcom.com(205.184.4.80) by dfw-ix14.ix.netcom.com via smap (V1.3)
	id rma028826; Mon Dec  1 18:04:06 1997
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
To: blitz-list <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Mon, 01 Dec 1997 18:01:01 -0600
Message-ID: <yam7274.76.3385368@smtp.ix.netcom.com>
In-Reply-To: <yam7274.240.127951040@mail.esoterica.pt>
X-Mailer: YAM 1.3.4 - Amiga Mailer by Marcel Beck
Subject: Re: Error: Out_of_Stack Space
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

Hi,

On 01-Dec-97, Eduardo David wrote:

>When making some recursive programming Blitz 2 Debuger gives the next error: 
> "Out_of_Stack Space".

>Anyone knows how to resolve this thing??

First check to be sure you are not allowing your program to leave any unused
addresses on the stack by leaving a for/next loop, a select/end select loop,
or a Gosub/Return without finishing.  If you must do this, you must also use a
Pop command, or the address is left on the stack and never taken off.  This
will eventually make the stack overflow and give the error.

Example:
a=1
.start

Gosub test
NPrint "You will never see this!"
mousewait
end

test
  nprint a
  a+1
  ;pop gosub     ;this will fix the error 
  goto start     ;you are leaving the routine here
Return           ;so this return is never reached


If this is not the problem, then your program simply requires more stack space
than the default.  Just set a higher value on the program's icon, or use the
Stack command from the CLI before running the program.  But if you do this,
and it only makes the program run a little longer before the error, then the
problem must be one of the above.

Bye...
-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
