Subject: Re: Execute_
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

On 11-Dec-97, Dave wrote:

>Hi  all
>       I`ve got I bit of a problem with the ` Execute_ ` command,
>       it stops my program until it gets a return value. 
>       I don`t want this I want something to do the same as Execute_
>       but not stop my program. The reason is because I want to
>       execute an arexx message sending program and my program then
>       take some action but it can`t do this because my program is
>       waiting for a result from execute_ so I`m stuck in an endless
>       wait.
>       Does anyone know a different command to use?


>Thanks for any comments

>DAVE

Try doing something like this:

cmd$="Run >NIL: <program>"
Execute_&cmd$,0,0

This will execute the string cmd$, but continue on....... using the "&" sign.


-- 

