> Hi  all
>        I`ve got I bit of a problem with the ` Execute_ ` command, it
>        stops my program until it gets a return value. I don`t want
>        this I want something to do the same as Execute_ but not stop
>        my program. The reason is because I want to execute an arexx
>        message sending program and my program then take some action
>        but it can`t do this because my program is waiting for a
>        result from execute_ so I`m stuck in an endless wait. Does
>        anyone know a different command to use?
> 
> 
Your should add the command "Run" before the rest of your execute 
string.  For example:

Execute_ "Run Sys:System/Format",0,0

This will run the format program but not hold up your own program 
until Format is quit.

Cheerio,

Mike.
