>    I just want to know what the structure of the InfoFileBlock type is,
> it`s in the Amigalibs.res thing i think... but i don`t want to use big
> libraries for such a small structure... so i`d rather just define it
> myself with:

 Only the required parts of amigalibs.res are included in your final 
executable, otherwise any program written with it would be a minimum 
of 270k (or whatever) in size. And they're not. And its 
FileInfoBlock.

 Using the above commands would actually make your executable smaller 
(probable only a few k) than if using the elmoredoslib, and there is 
examples of this kind of thing on the BUM disks or whatever, called 
mydir.bb and mydir2.bb.


Farewell, for now,

.oO David McMinn Oo.
