Hiya ppl!

I'm trying to do something here, without any luck :(

I'm trying to use the Copy command (AmigaDOS), to copy the whole of ENVARC: to
ENV:. I need to know when it has finished. I need to continue on a loop
though, so I can update the Busy.mcc.

This is what I'm doing:

cmd$="Run >NIL: Copy ENVARC: ENV: ALL"
Execute_ &cmd$,0,0
goto endbit 

endbit:

Repeat
ev.l=MUIEvent            ; So that Busy.mcc keeps beeing "busy", and moving ;)
msg=FindTask_("Copy")

until msg = ?


Now, it doesn't seem to get ANYTHING. msg that is. Has anyone got a bit of
source code that can tell whether Copy is running or not? I really need it!
-- 

