Content-Type: text/plain; charset=iso-8859-1
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable

Hi me!

>I'm making a program which should open a font choosed by the user. How c=
an I
>know if that font exists before using the LoadFont command? Or is there =
the
>way to know if LoadFont fails to open a font?

I found the solution myself. I'm sending it to the list in case there are=

people interested in it:

  DEFTYPE .TextAttr ta

  ta\ta_Name=3DFONTNAME$
  ta\ta_YSize=3DFONTSIZE
  ta\ta_Style=3D0
  ta\ta_Flags=3D#FPF_DESIGNED

  *tf.TextFont=3DOpenDiskFont_(ta)
  If *tf
    FONTSIZE=3D*tf\tf_YSize
    CloseFont_ (*tf)
  Else
    FindScreen 0
    *Scr.Screen=3DPeek.l(Addr Screen(0))
    FONTNAME$=3DPeek$(*Scr\Font\ta_Name)
    FONTSIZE=3D*Scr\Font\ta_YSize
  EndIf

  LoadFont 0,FONTNAME$,FONTSIZE

-- =

Best regards,

Luca.

   ___________________________________________
  |                                           |
  |   =3D-=3D-=3D-=3D-=3D  LUKE'S PROJECTS  =3D-=3D-=3D-=3D-=3D   |
