Hi Luca, On 04-Sep-95 you wrote...

>I'm making a program which should open a font choosed by the user. How can I
>know if that font exists before using the LoadFont command? Or is there the
>way to know if LoadFont fails to open a font?

Use the command "Exists" to see if the file/font is there.
Eg
   If Exists("FONTS:Bogus Font Name.font") = True
      ;Load font
   Else
      ;Don't load font, and say something nice to the user
   EndIf
   
If you use the ASLFontRequest then you will filter out this error and make
the users life easier.

Bye.
--
Matt Daniels
mattd@underused.u-net.com



@ENDNODE
