X-Mailer: YAM 1.3.4 - Amiga Mailer by Marcel Beck
Subject: Re: Fonts!!!
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

Hi Luca,

On 04-Sep-95, Luca Carminati wrote:
>Hi mates!

>I'm making a program which should open a font choosed by the user. How can I
>know if that font exists before using the LoadFont command? Or is there the
>way to know if LoadFont fails to open a font?

If you are using the ASL font requestor, it will only show fonts which do
exist in the current Fonts: assign.  Although you can type in any name in the
string gadget, the requestor will pick a different name if the one you type in
does not exist.  So it should be safe to assume that any font name returned by
the ASL fontrequestor does exist.

To double check, you can do this:

(get selection from ASLfontRequestor)
check$="Fonts:"+(fontname$ returned by ASLFontRequestor)
If Exists (check$)
  (go ahead and load the font)
Else
  (use default font, or whatever...)
Endif

I have an example code that shows how to open the font requestor using a
taglist, so you can specify the requestor size, if you want colour selection,
maximum and minimum font sizes you want to show, if you want only
non-proportional fonts shown, etc.  This also allows you to set the default
font and size shown (instead of always Topaz 8), and can also remember the
last font, size, colours, etc. that were selected, and open with these
hi-lighted.

If you want this, email to me direct.
-- 
