Hi Eduardo,

> So you are seeing what is the problem.
> If I call function "1" Blitz gives an error saying that can't find function
> "3". If I move function "1" after function "3" then is function "2" that
> can't find function "1".

> This is a big problem!!!
> Isn't there any command in Blitz that works like the command "Forward" in
> Pascal ?

It's not a big problem. You just have to make sure your code is
properly structured. The way I learnt how to program properly was
using a structured system called JSP and if you follow the rules
of this programming technique it's impossible to ever come accross
your problem. When C and other new languages came they introduced 
prototyping which allows you to get away with bad structure.

Can you give an example of why you'd need to call a function
below when you can't simply rearange your functions in
the correct order? Foundation has over 200 Functions and
I've never had a serious problem.

Chers,

Paul

