If you do that, you end up doing an infinite loop anyway, so it`s 
better that you`re not allowed to!
:)
Anyway, this is an old blitz compiler bug, it SHOULD be doing a 
preliminary pass for function names, but it doesn`t. :/

Now, for a solution (?)
Use only one function that calls itself...

If your function calls there are conditional then nest the appropriate
code in if/endif(!)
	or
use


function 1()
	;3(x)
	function return x
end function
function 2()
	;1(x)
	function return x
end function
function 3()
	;2(x)
	function return x
end function
Function 0()
	0(1(2(3())))
end function




or something :)


Christos Dimitrakakis (aka Olethros)
Electronic Engineer,
Software Developer for the Amiga computer
University of Essex
http://esewww.essex.ac.uk/~cdimita



