On 19-Dec-97, Paul Burkey wrote:

> > > have made it even better. So on my wish list for Blitz 3 would
> > > be to remove the goto command! :)

> > Then I would use bra instead. ;)

> I think the BRA command is fine because it's an Asm call. If you
> use Asm then jumps like this are fine. Asm is a low level language
> so the use of BRA is part of the structure. If you're just using
> BRA by itself to just about willy nilly then thats also bad coding.
> I'm not an Asm programmer but I'm sure you'll find that BRA is
> used as part of a set of commands which make up structured code.
> For example, my current project is 20,000 lines long and it doesn't
> use a single Goto. However if I compile this and then check using
> a Disassembler I'll find that BRA is used quite a lot. This isn't
> because I'm fooling myself about structure, it's because computers
> work that way. Exploiting this is the job of the Asm programmer
> who is perfectly free to do what it takes to get the Asm working
> as fast as possible. Trying to do this with a high level language
> is not so fruitful.

Yes! I think that would be better that there would not be goto at all.
If there would not be goto command (it's translated to bra or jmp depedin=
g
the length of the two locations) new coders would learn the "right way" t=
o
code. And still advanced users could use bra (or jmp) if needed.

