On 04-Jan-80, Julian Kinraid wrote:
> Hi,

> >be to remove the goto command! :)

> Why?  That just restricts things even more.  Until Blitz becomes a _lot=
_
more
> advanced, Goto/Gosub still come in handy.  I generally don't use them, =
but
in
> one program I have a couple of statements that have about 20 SHARED
variables,
> because you can't have global variables.  Then there is the bug in
> statement/functions that under certain conditions, will trash one of th=
e
> passed variables (I've fixed this bug though.)  You can't have static
> variables in procedures, so you have to make an extra SHARED varia
> ble for that.

> It's things like these that need to be fixed, and until they are,
Goto/Gosubs
> will still come in handy.

The Gosub was never under threat, but the goto is a command that should b=
e
avoided. And if you give a beginner who don't have proper knoledge of
programming, he will use way too much gotos in his code. This is the reso=
n
why that goto should have been left out. Because the inline assembler, yo=
u
can go around it just using bra and jmp. This would prevent that
overwhelming goto using in the beginners code. I certainly used too much
those, and thats why my progs where never properly made, and debugging wa=
s
real pain in the ass.

Gosub is a whole different case, because it represents the basic subrouti=
ne
programming. The gosub turns into bsr or jsr and the return to rts.

Statements and functions are just group of asm code that completes the
bsr/jsr to rts subroutine to make it more structural.

