>of coding. I do have a problem with Goto which doesn't fit into any
>form of structure. I'm just being a bit facetious when I talk about
>taking away Goto from the language but it would be nice to loose the
>old BASIC origins.=20

If beginners learnt how to write structured code, they wouldn't need =
Goto.  But if you just remove Goto, they aren't going to suddenly learn =
how to write structured code, and it will make it more difficult for =
beginners because they will have to find out what to use instead of =
goto.  Leave Goto alone, and put a section on structured code in the =
manual IMHO.

I would love to see Blitz break the shackles of old BASIC ideas and =
become a more powerful language.  The BASIC language on the Macs at =
school was the worst thing I have ever seen, and probably did a lot for =
making students _avoid_ programming :)  Blitz at the moment would have =
been a lot better, but with some work, it could be excellent.

Merry Christmas,
Julian Kinraid






