 Have you ever written a piece of software, which uses shared 
variables in some functions, ran it only to find it not working. You 
spend ages checking the code and the spelling of variables, but you 
can't find out whats wrong, until you realise that you have not 
shared a variable in a function it should be shared in? Verrrrry 
annoying.

> > Static variables are global constants.
> 
>   Well someone said static variables can`t be used in a Function
>   but if constants is what they mean I have no problem using them
>   in functions.
  
 Constants are always global. Static variables (in C anyway) can be 
used like this:
	As globals, can only be used in the source file they exist in
	or in functions where they retain their value between function calls

Farewell, for now,

