Mime-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: TEXT/PLAIN; CHARSET=US-ASCII


On Mon, 22 Dec 1997 05:08:38 +0500 Paul Burkey 
<paul%sneech.demon.co.uk@uk.ac.essex.mailhost> wrote:
> I'd be happy to see an example where
> a Goto is needed.
> 
Here's a funny one:
A jumptable.
A bit like a case statement I guess, but not quite the same
since it can change dynamically.
so if you have an array
jtable.l(32)
you jump to point x in it
by
	getreg d0,jtable(x)	;If goto is like other blitz
	TokeJsr Goto		;commands it should accept d0
				;and not a0, as would be more
				;"natural"
or even
	TokeJsr	Gosub		

Never tested this with goto, but should work :)




Christos Dimitrakakis (aka Olethros)
Electronic Engineer,
Software Developer for the Amiga computer
University of Essex
http://esewww.essex.ac.uk/~cdimita



@ENDNODE
