On 22-Dec-97, Julian Kinraid wrote:

> If beginners learnt how to write structured code, they wouldn't need Go=
to. =

> But if you just remove Goto, they aren't going to suddenly learn how to=

write
> structured code, and it will make it more difficult for beginners becau=
se
they
> will have to find out what to use instead of goto.  Leave Goto alone, a=
nd
put
> a section on structured code in the manual IMHO.

Well beginners will always make "bad" code, but they learn! But if you gi=
ve
a choice to use goto or make structured code most will choose goto. This
because it's "easier" to do so... :(

The properly made guide or something could still better the situation.
I think the axamples of using certain type of commands compared to other
alternatives would also be prity useful.

> I would love to see Blitz break the shackles of old BASIC ideas and bec=
ome a
> more powerful language.  The BASIC language on the Macs at school was t=
he
> worst thing I have ever seen, and probably did a lot for making student=
s
> _avoid_ programming :)  Blitz at the moment would have been a lot bette=
r,
but
> with some work, it could be excellent.

I think the new blitz should be called just "Blitz" not basic any more!
But that's just my opinion.

