On 22-Dec-97, Paul Burkey wrote:

> > Here's a funny one: A jumptable.
> > A bit like a case statement I guess, but not quite the same
> > since it can change dynamically.
> > jtable.l(32)
> >
> > getreg d0,jtable(x)
> > TokeJsr Goto

And now if some fansy guy starts to make jumptables CLEAR the CACHES afte=
r
making the table!!!

> Well this is almost like going into Asm for speed but using
> the Basic command to make a point ;) If you wanted to do this sort
> of thing then pure Asm would be better. I'm not so good with Asm
> but couldn't you do somthing like this:

> GetReg a0,jtable(x)
> BRA a0

And that's faster too. and you can change it special gosub select->case
system by using bsr instead. (I think if you do JTables as these you shou=
ld
use jmp/jsr to be sure that the jump goes where it should be!!)

if using jmp/jsr the entry size is 6 bytes and bra/bsr table size is 4
bytes.

