Date: Fri, 02 Jan 1998 00:13:29 GMT0
Message-ID: <yam7306.1482.3310784@mail.geocities.com>
X-Mailer: YAM 1.3.5 [020] - Amiga Mailer by Marcel Beck
Organization: Private UK Amiga Geezer!
Subject: General questions/probs ...
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

Right, so using SELECT...END SELECT's are faster than using a group of
IF...ENDIF's ?

My program uses Blitz Mode with the mouse enabled. The thing is, the pointer
doesn't move very fast - can I add a value of 1 (or whatever) to the mouse's
current moving position, thus speeding it up? I can't seem to find a command
that'll let me move the pointer relative to it's current position ....

My main screen (this is a diskmag (creator), by the way) consists of 4
coplists (title, main viewing area, control panel and scroll-text). I need to
the move mouse pointer from the main viewing area and the control panel as
smooth as possible. I'm currently using: 

   SetInt 5
      DisplaySprite SPR_COPLIST,0,MouseX,MouseY,1
   End SetInt

When the mouse is moved to the bottom edge of the main viewing area, I change
SPR_COPLIST to the value of the Control Panel's coplist number, thus
displaying it in the Control Panel coplist (eh?). Is there a smoother/better
way of doing this?

When the diskmag starts, the user has the option of displaying start-up
pictures (upto 300 - at the moment). I'm using a seperate program to grab the
pictures' size/height/bitplanes/etc and then write them into the main config
file. In-which the diskmag engine does the following to determine the format
of the pic (sorry if it's laid-out in a mess, I'm using a crappy
non-proportional font):

    AGA.b = CheckAGA                      ;AGA chipset available ?
    dum.l = PIX(i)\ViewFlags               ;IFFWidth/Height/etc viewflags.

    If PIX(i)\Colours>5 OR AGA=True Then VFlags.l=$10000 Else PIX(i)\Fade=1
    If (dum.l&32768) Then VFlags.l+$100   ;HiRes
    If (dum.l&32)    Then VFlags.l+$200   ;SHiRes
    If (dum.l&2048)  Then VFlags.l+$80    ;HAM

I'm using the IFFWidth/IFFHeight/IFFDepth/etc commands to find the dimentions
of the picture file, but the problem is, the format's not compatible with the
DisplayLib. So does anyone know how I can convert the flags or something?
Because the above method is bound to fall over!

I'm really making use of this BlitzList (don't worry, I've got more questions
to come!) :)

-- 
.------------------------------------.------------------------------------.
| A1200/28Mhz/2+4Mb/K56Flex/HyperCOM | Amiga Blitz 2 coder type UK bloke! |
| EMAIL: BootBlock@GeoCities.com     | www.geocities.com/SiliconValley/   |
| "NightLife BBS" - online soon!     | Lab/4868/index.html - almost ready |
`------------------------------------"------------------------------------'



@ENDNODE
