X-Mailer: YAM 1.3.4 [040] - Amiga Mailer by Marcel Beck
Subject: Re: GetaShape
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

Hi,

> However, attempting to blit these shapes revealed that some of them were not
> all there, with lines missing or bitplanes missing (sometimes the background
> colour picked up OK and the ink was left out). The shapes corrupted are
> different each time you run the program.

It's a well known bug. If you turn the cache of your 030 off it will
work okay. I never had a reson to look into a solution for this but there
must be an easy way to get around the problem. A few solutions you could
try would be to grab the shapes save them, flush them and then load them
back. Maybe a more simple version of hat idea is possible but the bug is
a real pain and it gets in the way of many ideas.

I only experienced it myself durring a short 3 week period of using an
030 on my machine. The 020 was okay and the 040 was okay so I guess it's
a problem with certain 030 caches. As a rough guess, are you using a
non Blizzard 030? If you're not then the problem is bigger than I thought.

Cheers,

Paul


