To: blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie
Message-ID: <009BE1D0.71A0CAF9.33@ice.sbu.ac.uk>
Subject: GetaShape


Hi there

Anyone know if GetaShape has any peculiarities? I wanted to put little text
lables, 3 characters each 24x8 pixels, at arbitrary locations on the screen,
so I decided to print them onto a bitmap, use getashape to cut them out and
then blit them where I wanted them. To test this I wrote the following code:

Bitmap 1,640,512,3 ;(only made it this big so I could show it on a screen)
BitmapOutput 1
Format "000":Colour 1,3
for f.l=0 to 1      ; two lines of 3 digit numbers
  for g.l=0 to 9    ; 000 to 009 and 010 to 019
     print f*10+g
  next
  nprint ""
next
for f=0 to 1
  for g=0 to 9
    GetaShape f*10+g,g*24,f*8,24,8
  next
next

However, attempting to blit these shapes revealed that some of them were not
all there, with lines missing or bitplanes missing (sometimes the background
colour picked up OK and the ink was left out). The shapes corrupted are
different each time you run the program.

I have solved the problem by adding the lines 

SaveShapes 0,19,"RAM:shapes"
LoadShapes 0,"RAM:shapes"

And the corruption disappears, so it seems you can't getashape and use it,
without saving it first and reloading it. Is this a known fact or should I
being doing something else before using getashape?

Cheers

Mike Child





@ENDNODE
