Content-Type: text/plain

Hi,

On 01-Dec-97, Paul Burkey wrote:

>> However, attempting to blit these shapes revealed that some of them were
not
>> all there, with lines missing or bitplanes missing (sometimes the
background
>> colour picked up OK and the ink was left out). The shapes corrupted are
>> different each time you run the program.

>It's a well known bug. If you turn the cache of your 030 off it will
>work okay. I never had a reson to look into a solution for this but there
>must be an easy way to get around the problem. A few solutions you could
>try would be to grab the shapes save them, flush them and then load them
>back. Maybe a more simple version of hat idea is possible but the bug is
>a real pain and it gets in the way of many ideas.

This might be related, although it has to do with sounds.  Two people with
030's had told me that my program's sound did not work correctly unless they
turned their caches off.  Then when I uploaded a new version, both wrote back
to say that now the sounds worked fine even with the caches on!  I couldn't
figure this out as I had not changed anything to do with the sounds at all.

I just went and looked at my code - the difference is now that my music mod is
loaded AFTER the sounds & shapes, and the one GetAShape command now comes
BEFORE the module is loaded.  Could this be related?  No one ever reported a
problem with the shapes, BTW.

Is it possible that loading the module causes the caches to flush, thus fixing
the problem?  And is there maybe some way to force the cache to flush?  Or
some way to disable the cache temporarily from within the program?
-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
