Message-ID: <009BE296.7C84CE3F.68@ice.sbu.ac.uk>
Subject: GetAShape, 030 caches etc.


Hi all, thanks for the replies...

Yes, my blitting problem vanishes if I disable the accelerator or just
turn off the caches.

My board IS a Blizzard, Mark IV 50mhz, got it about spring this year.

using 

SaveShapes 0,19,"RAM:shapes"
LoadShapes 0,"RAM:shapes"

AFTER using GetAShape and BEFORE trying to blit solves the problem without
disabling the caches, and it makes no difference whether you free the shapes
after saving them and before reloading them or not.

Curt wrote:

>I just went and looked at my code - the difference is now that my music mod is
>loaded AFTER the sounds & shapes, and the one GetAShape command now comes
>BEFORE the module is loaded.  Could this be related?  No one ever reported a
>problem with the shapes, BTW.

>Is it possible that loading the module causes the caches to flush, thus fixing
>the problem?  And is there maybe some way to force the cache to flush?  Or
>some way to disable the cache temporarily from within the program?

This is my reasoning too. If the corruption is caused by the caches getting
messed up, then clearing the cache completely ought to solve the problem.
It seems likely (at least intuitively) that the load/save operations are
doing this. It'll do for me, though some kind of ClearCache instruction would
be preferable...

Cheers all

TTFN 
Mike Child




@ENDNODE
