Hi Mike,

On 02-Dec-97, mike.child@sbu.ac.uk wrote:


>using 

>SaveShapes 0,19,"RAM:shapes"
>LoadShapes 0,"RAM:shapes"

>AFTER using GetAShape and BEFORE trying to blit solves the problem without
>disabling the caches, and it makes no difference whether you free the shapes
>after saving them and before reloading them or not.

Well, I am not sure, but I think if you reload a shape using the same number
as a previous shape will then give you 2 copies of the shape in memory,
wasting chip ram.  Also if this is true, when you program exits, only the
memory of the new shapes will be freed by Blitz.

Another thought, since you are using these shapes just to copy text:

Have you considered using FNSfonts to print with instead?  This can print to
any pixel location on your bitmap, and offers the option to center the text on
a particular point (like the center of your circle).  This would eliminate all
the GetAShapes and also the need for another bitmap.




-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
