X-Mailer: Microsoft Internet Mail 4.70.1155
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit



     Okay, here is a small function to determine the number of colors
     in a palette-file:

     Function.w GetPaletteSize{palname$}
       numbitplanes.w=0
       If ReadFile(0,palname$)
          FileInput 0
          For rep.w=1 to 29
             numbitplanes=Asc(Edit$(1))
          Next rep
          CloseFile 0
          Vwait 4
          DefaultInput
       End If
       Function Return 2^numbitplanes
     End Function 

     Use like this...

     numcolors.w=GetPaletteSize{yourpalettename$}
     if numcolors=0 then the palette could not be found/opened.

     This should work with pictures, brushes and palette-files as the 
     header-info seems to be consistent for all three file-types.


      Take  care,   
      GARFIELD
