Hi,

>      Function.w GetPaletteSize{palname$}
>        numbitplanes.w=0
>        If ReadFile(0,palname$)
>           FileInput 0
>           For rep.w=1 to 29
>              numbitplanes=Asc(Edit$(1))
>           Next rep
>           CloseFile 0
>           Vwait 4
>           DefaultInput
>        End If
>        Function Return 2^numbitplanes
>      End Function 

Hmm, seems to be hardcoded to read the 29th byte. I'm sure that'll
fail eventually unless the CMAP is always in the same location.
Searching for "CMAP" and reading from there is probably safer.

Anyway, heres a modified version of the above function that doesn't
have to read 29 bytes from the file. It uses FileSeek and ReadMem.

Function.w GetPaletteSize{palname$}
  numbitplanes.b=0
  If ReadFile(0,palname$)
    FileSeek 0,28
    ReadMem 0,&numbitplanes.b,1
    CloseFile 0
  End If
  Function Return 2^numbitplanes
End Function

Appart from that it does the same thing.

Cheers,

Paul


-- 
