>    header IDs instead of examining the 29th-byte.

>    Thanks for the info!! =


Just a little add on info:

The file is structured like this:

0"FORM"; At the very beginning
4Size of; File size-8
8Identifyer; This one points out which kind of file this is.
; ILMBBMHD points that this is Craphics related.
16Size of ; Size of the following data.
20+(16)ID; Next header identifier.
24+(16) Size of; Size of the following data.

And so on


