   projects.

   The routines that I already have work perfectly fine for my needs as
   I  already know the # of colors in my palettes and the 29th-byte also
   works fine with my palettes, brushes and pictures...


   Anyway, thanks for this additional info as does take a while to
   "decode" these formats. I simply examined the first 64bytes of
   several palettes, pictures and brushes and noted which values were
   the same and which were different. This is how I discovered "CMAP"
   and "ILBM", "BMHD", but didn't bother to decode what those offset
   values actually were as they were not needed to extract the palette
   RGB values which are stored in a very straight-forward and sensible
   matter...

   With you guys being so familiar with these IFF structures I would
   think you must already have the code which Alvaro needs, so I won't
   waste my time writing them and "reinventing the wheel".

   If not, then from the info listed above, it looks like offsets 16 and 20
   are the key here Alvaro...

  
