@NODE "Mail.230" "GT gadgets and VisualPrefs"
Number: 42
Return-path: <blitz-list-return-1558-scott=online.u-net.com@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Envelope-to: scott@online.u-net.com
Delivery-date: Tue, 30 Dec 1997 17:52:40 +0000
Received: from orca.ucd.ie [137.43.4.16] 
	id 0xn5qJ-0000YX-00; Tue, 30 Dec 1997 17:52:39 +0000
Received: (qmail 5213 invoked by alias); 30 Dec 1997 17:52:26 -0000
Mailing-List: contact blitz-list-help@netsoc.ucd.ie; run by ezmlm
Delivered-To: mailing list blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie
Received: (qmail 5207 invoked from network); 30 Dec 1997 17:52:24 -0000
Received: from mailhost.ldn1.uk.internetfci.net (195.74.65.20)
  by orca.ucd.ie with SMTP; 30 Dec 1997 17:52:24 -0000
Received: from thenet.co.uk (awingrove@dip-195-74-66-98.thenet.co.uk [195.74.66.98])
	for <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>; Tue, 30 Dec 1997 17:53:02 GMT
From: Alexander Wingrove <awingrove@thenet.co.uk>
Reply-To: awingrove@thenet.co.uk
To: Blitz List <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Tue, 30 Dec 1997 17:50:20 -0000
Message-ID: <yam7303.1043.30185208@smtp.thenet.co.uk>
X-Mailer: YAM 1.3.5 [040] - Amiga Mailer by Marcel Beck
Subject: GT gadgets and VisualPrefs
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-type: multipart/mixed; boundary="BOUNDARY.7303.1043.30185208.1"


Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.

This message was composed on an Amiga using the YAM mailer.
YAM is available at http://bitcom.ch/~mbeck/

--BOUNDARY.7303.1043.30185208.1
Content-Type: text/plain

Hi all,

I am working on the new GadTools section for the FAQ. However, I have run
across a problem. When I use the attached code with VisualPrefs 1.3A
running, the debugger pops up telling me it cannot free the GTList at the
end. If I remove VisualPrefs, it works fine. Does this happen with anyone
else? Does anyone know what the problem might be?

Thanks,
Alex

-- 
+-- Alex Wingrove / awingrove@thenet.co.uk --+

[      www.thenet.co.uk/~awingrove/blitz/       ]
[ Blitz Program Collection  and  Blitz List FAQ ]


--BOUNDARY.7303.1043.30185208.1
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=iso-8859-1; name="gt_example.bb2"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable
Content-Description: GadTools example

WBStartup
NoCli

; set up the contstants
#GTL =3D 0
#WIN =3D 0
#SCR =3D 0

; always use ID's of 50 and above
#ID_BUTTON    =3D 50
#ID_CHECKBOX  =3D 51
#ID_CYCLE     =3D 52
#ID_INTEGER   =3D 53
#ID_MX        =3D 54
#ID_NUMBER    =3D 55
#ID_PALETTE   =3D 56
#ID_SCROLLER  =3D 57
#ID_SLIDER    =3D 58
#ID_STRING    =3D 59
#ID_TEXT      =3D 60

WBenchToFront_
FindScreen #SCR
AddIDCMP #IDCMP_MOUSEMOVE|#IDCMP_INTUITICKS ; needed if using Slider or S=
croller
Window #WIN,0,15,400,200,$140e,"GadTools Example",1,2

; declare GT gadgets after the window has been opened

GTButton    #GTL,#ID_BUTTON, 5, 5, 100, 15, "GTButton", #PLACETEXT_IN

GTCheckBox  #GTL,#ID_CHECKBOX, 95, 25, 15, 15, "GTCheckBox", $100|#PLACET=
EXT_LEFT
            ; $100 in the flags means the checkbox will initially be chec=
ked

GTCycle     #GTL,#ID_CYCLE, 70, 40, 100, 15, "GTCycle", #PLACETEXT_LEFT, =
"Fred|Wilma|Barney|Betty"

GTTags #STRINGA_Justification, #STRINGRIGHT ; align the number to the rig=
ht
GTInteger   #GTL,#ID_INTEGER, 85, 60, 80, 15, "GTInteger", #PLACETEXT_LEF=
T, 123456

GTTags #GTMX_Spacing, 2 ; 2 pixel spacing between items
GTMX        #GTL,#ID_MX, 5, 80, 1, 1, "", #PLACETEXT_RIGHT, "Fred|Wilma|B=
arney|Betty", 0 ; fred is initially active
            ; width and height on GTMX are ignored

GTTags #GTNM_Justification, #GTJ_RIGHT ; Position number to the right
GTNumber    #GTL,#ID_NUMBER, 80, 125, 80, 15, "GTNumber", #PLACETEXT_LEFT=
, 123456

GTTags #GTPA_IndicatorHeight, 6 ; indicator to show selected colour
GTPalette   #GTL,#ID_PALETTE, 270, 5, 100, 25, "GTPalette", #PLACETEXT_LE=
FT, 3, 0 ; colour 0 is initially active

GTScroller  #GTL,#ID_SCROLLER, 270, 35, 100, 10, "GTScroller", $800|#PLAC=
ETEXT_LEFT, 32, 64, 16
            ; $800 in the flags adds arrows to the scroller
            ; Total is the overall area for the scroller ( e.g. 640 for a=
 bitmap 640 pixels wide )
            ; Visible is the amount of the toal area that is visible at o=
ne time ( e.g. 320 pixels )
            ; Top is the start position of the visible area ( e.g. 160 to=
 start the visible area in the middle of the bitmap )

f$=3D"%ld"
GTTags #GTSL_LevelFormat, &f$, #GTSL_MaxLevelLen, 2, #GTSL_LevelPlace, #P=
LACETEXT_LEFT ; add a number to the slider
GTSlider    #GTL,#ID_SLIDER, 270, 65, 100, 10, "GTSlider", #PLACETEXT_ABO=
VE, 1, 10, 1 ; starts slider at position 1

GTString    #GTL,#ID_STRING, 270, 80, 80, 15, "GTString", #PLACETEXT_LEFT=
, 50, "Fred"

GTText      #GTL,#ID_TEXT, 270, 100, 80, 15, "GTText", #PLACETEXT_LEFT, "=
Fred"

; finally, attach the gadgets to the window
AttachGTList #GTL,#WIN

; bevelbox only works after the GT list has been attached to a window
GTBevelBox #GTL, 5, 155, 380, 12, 1 ; 1 is a recessed bevel, 0 isn't

;or if you want to use the different frame types...
*win.Window =3D Peek.l(Addr Window(#WIN))
vi.l =3D GetVisualInfoA_(Peek.l(Addr Screen(#SCR)),0)
; for each bevelbox, set up a tag list and call DrawBevelBoxA
; ( if FrameType and Recessed do not change between bevel boxes, you can =
re-use the taglist )
InitTagList 0, 5 : Use TagList 0
AddTags #GTBB_Recessed, 0 ; remove this line to make the bevel non-recess=
ed
AddTags #GTBB_FrameType, #BBFT_RIDGE ; options are BUTTON, RIDGE or ICOND=
ROPBOX
AddTags #GT_VisualInfo, vi
DrawBevelBoxA_ *win\RPort, 5, 172, 380, 12, TagList(0)
Free TagList 0

; standard wait-for-close loop
finish.b =3D False
Repeat
  ev.l =3D WaitEvent
  Select ev
    Case $200
      finish =3D True
  End Select
Until finish

DetachGTList #GTL

Free GTList #GTL

End


--BOUNDARY.7303.1043.30185208.1--





@ENDNODE
