Subject: Re: how Can i use "" ?
In-Reply-To: <yam7277.1238.140051640@post8.tele.dk>
Message-ID: <Pine.SUN.3.91.971204170719.11858A-100000@chebucto.ns.ca>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: TEXT/PLAIN; charset=US-ASCII

On Thu, 4 Dec 1997, Allan Pedersen wrote:

> Execute_ "C:XFD >NIL: "+s$+d$,0,0
> There are no problems if the source name is (Mod.Modname). But when its called
> (Mod.Mod Name) i have problems!!

You should be able to use the ASCII code for " instead, try Execute_ 
"C:XFD >NIL: "+chr$(34)+s$+d$+chr$(34),0,0).  I think the ASCII code for 
" is 34... :)

Good luck,

