To anyone who didn't like my message and feel angered or annoyed
by it, I apologize for wasting your time.

On the other hand, to anyone who liked my message, I hope that
it brightened up your day a bit. =3D)  It was all in good fun,
really.  Sorry if you couldn't sense the overflowing spoonful of
sarcasm.

It has been ... one of "those days."  I just found myself lashing
out at the first non-Net-Etiquette-following person I saw.

Oh, to James Boyd: Doomed to Obscurity is a zine that is usually
characterized as using entirely lower-case.  That's why it's in lower
case at the bottom of my signature.

And I know that "u" is a widely-used online abbreviation for "you." =3D)
I'm very used to it being used by ignorant newbies on BBSes in my
area code, so I get very touchy when someone uses it.

I also apologize to "comunion."  Sorry it had to be you that I lashed
out at.  However, you really aren't following the rules of mailing
lists or Usenet or FidoNet.  Perhaps you should read up on your
"Netiquette."  If this were a moderated message base, the =

moderator would have yelled at you for posting multiple messages
containing only "Thank you for the URL!"

I'm not a bad guy, really.

-- =


