Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.

This message was composed on an Amiga using the YAM mailer.
YAM is available at http://bitcom.ch/~mbeck/

--BOUNDARY.7288.914.2382744.1
Content-Type: text/plain

On 14-Dec-97, Paul Burkey wrote:
>Hi,

>Can somone explain how to use RawKey for detecting the last
>"key press"? I spent a while trying to get it to work but
>it alwas returned 0. I then discovered that "EventCode" did
>just what I wanted. What is the point or what is the
>difference between RawKey and EventCode?

>Cheers,

>Paul

You can use Inkey$, EventCode, or KeyCode to read the keypresses.
Try the small test code below.  You will find that Inkey$ responds
to all character keys (Alt A gives a different value than just A),
EventCode ignores everything but the key (Alt A, shift A, Ctrl A
all give the same value), and KeyCode responds to all except the
shift key.

KeyCode and EventCode also can recognize for example a number was 
entered from the numeric keypad or the main keyboard.  
Inkey$ does not recognize this.

I used Event rather than WaitEvent because I'm assuming you don't
want the program to stop and wait for a keypress.
-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



--BOUNDARY.7288.914.2382744.1
Content-Type: text/plain; name="KeyPress.test"

WBenchToFront_
WbToScreen 0
NoCli
Window 0,100,20,200,200,$8|$1000|$400,"Event Test",1,0

Repeat
  ev.l=Event     ;catch all events and save in queque
  If ev=$400     ;read next queque'd keypress
    a$=Inkey$
    b$=Str$(EventCode)
    c$=Str$(KeyCode)
    NPrint "Inkey$   : ",a$
    WPrintScroll
    NPrint "EventCode: ",b$
    WPrintScroll
    NPrint "KeyCode  : ",c$
    WPrintScroll
    NPrint "================="
    WPrintScroll
  EndIf
Until ev=$200
End




--BOUNDARY.7288.914.2382744.1--




@ENDNODE
