On 15-Dec-97, Curt Esser wrote:

Oooops!  I forgot to mention about RawKey!

If used in the example shown with the Event command, it will give (on my
system anyway) the same results as EventCode.

If used without the Event Command:

EventCode gives the code of the last event, keypress or other event.
RawKey gives always the last keypress event.

So, if a user pressed "a", "b", and "c", and clicked the mouse before you got
around to checking, RawKey will give the code for "c", but EventCode will give
the code for mouse button.  Either way, all the other inputs are ignored.


-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
