X-Priority: 3
X-MSMail-Priority: Normal
X-Mailer: Microsoft Outlook Express 4.71.1008.3
X-MimeOle: Produced By Microsoft MimeOLE Engine V4.71.1008.3

Hi Alvaro,=20

>I've had a little idea. Is there anyway someone could write a little =
program
>which would scan through an executbale (created by Blitz), and give out =
a
>little output to tell the user, which libs have been used for that =
program,
>eg:
>
>Libs used
>=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D
>
>EFMUILib
>DOMethodBB
>etc

This might be hard, because an executable won't have any information =
saying 'EFMUILib is used', so it would be hard to find an identifier for =
each library.

I gave some code to Mike Carter that scans through source code and finds =
out which libraries are used (only the lib numbers, not the library =
name).  He's already got some code that finds what libraries are on a =
system.  Combine these two, and you know what libraries your source code =
uses.

Ciao,
Julian Kinraid




@ENDNODE
