Organization: Private UK Amiga Geezer!
Subject: IF...THENs
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

In the main loop of one of my programs (BlitzAMC), I've get two sets of 14 (or
so) IF...THENs. Is there another way I can do this comparing but FASTER ?  As
I think this may be contributing to slowing the program down (okay, so you
can't notice it, but wouldn't it be best to try and get everything running as
fast as possible?).

How in the name of arse do you (well, me) read a GTMX gadget?? I've tried to
grab the eventcode being returned, but it don't return `owt, like!

I've read some of them BlitzList compilations from a while back, and I can
remember some Blitz Lister's talking about standardising a Help Mode type of
thing. What's happened to this - has it been completed? If so, where can I get
the required files to implement this into me own programs (because the one
I've done requires a string gadget in my GUI to display the help text) ?

Oh, I've created some code (took ages!) to display some help when the pointer
is over gadgets and things. Does anyone want a copy (I can post it here, don't
worry, the source is quite small!) ?

Does anyone remember GadgetToolsBox (by Tim Caldwell) that came on a BUM a
while ago? 
Is there a later version of this available? Coz it's ace!

Any jobs going out there for a GUI coder (because I heard from
ex-Dick@emarkt.com) that Desktop Corruption were looking for some) ? I want
one/ten/hundreds !!  I'm pretty good, honest!

Can someone tell me where to get the latest libraries (I'm a registered
Blitz/BSS user)?

Merry Chrimble everyone!

