On 24-Dec-97, Christopher Jonko wibbled:

>Try the structure like that:
>IF war1
>  bla1
>ELSE
>  IF war2
>    bla2
>  ELSE
>    IF war3
>      bla3
>    ELSE
>...
>and go on. BUT yoy have to place most important IF at the begin of loop
>(to get faster good result).
>The second one method is using SELECT...CASE:

By first glance, this looks like it will be slower, but I'm not sure. Anyway,
there'll be loads of EndIf's at the end! While we're on the subject of
EndIf's... what's the difference between "EndIF" and "End IF" ? Does the
latter use a tiny bit more memory/space?

>SELECT variable
>  CASE 1: bla1
>  CASE 2: bla2
>  CASE 7: bla3
>  ...
>END SELECT

I've heard from numerous other people that this is faster. But, would it suit
a diskmag engine that's got other things going on (clock, scroll-text, etc) ?

>opening amiga guide database directly on MY screen. It works very fine.
>I've very good example if you want (my "little" help consist of two
>files 150kB and 70kB).
>If you could send me your help code - I'm collecting all things about
>BLITZ. I've VERY BIG collection of progs :)

Right thanks, send me your "little" (ha! It's fat git size!) progs. I'll have
a nice perv at them! :)

Okay, I'm about recode my Help Control thingy (it was only for my purpose,
thus it was totally messy!) and I'll include it as an "attachment" ....



>Merry Christmas!

Hey, it's Christmas day now! Uh-oh, Mr Vampire 2 is gonna be on in 2 mins,
I'd better hurry up  .....

