Content-Type: text/plain

On 17-Dec-97, David Mcminn wrote:
> Does anyone know if there is a Java interpreter on the Amiga? Or a 
>Java compiler?

At the moment there is only Guavac and Kaffe. These are a free compiler and
interpretor. They don't have support for any graphics or AWT (advanced window
toolkit) support but they supposedly work (though I couldn't get them
going...might need an 040). There are supposed to be two Java Virtual Machines
being released in the next few months or so. And Java support is supposedly
going to be added to Storm C. Do a search on the web for Java and Amiga and
you'll find a pile of pages.

> I think that I'm going to try to write a Java interpreter using 
>Blitz.

> Comments, anyone?

I don't think it's worth the effort :]
But good luck anyway.

Andrew
