Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.

This message was composed on an Amiga using the YAM mailer.
YAM is available at http://bitcom.ch/~mbeck/

--BOUNDARY.7304.2331.3359816.1
Content-Type: text/plain

A long while ago, me and a friend starting on coding a game that was supposed
to be an Amiga version of the PlayStation's Destruction Derby (you plus pooter
cars going round and spanking into each other). Me friend just only got back
in touch with me, but the maths in the game is a bit too much for him. I'm
totally poo at maths and coding games in general (I'm a utils bloke, me), so,
I was wondering... how about we all (you peeps on the Blitz List) start this
up as *our* project?

This is basically the game at the moment ....

The game is viewed overhead (raytraced gfx - cols had to be cut down due to
major slow-down) and the player's task is to crash into the other cars and
cause as much damage as possible, without getting their car wrecked.

If you've seen Burnout by Vulcan, then you'll know what I'm getting at. Except
the main arena is 2 screens high and 2 screens wide (4 screens in total) and
viewed in LoRes 230x256 with a 64 colour palette (only a very small amount of
colours are actually being used, at this moment). Also, the game hasn't got a
name yet - Derby is just a temp name.

There's two versions at present - the one player full-screen version, and the
two player split-screen version.

The main player's car uses 31 shapes, but it'll have to be increased to 62 for
extra smoothness. If ya know what I mean!

I've got the main car bombing around the arena, plus some skids and things,
but I just can't do the wall collisions. Also, how the hell is the computer's
AI gonna be done??

I've included the source code in this posting for you all to have a look at
(one player version - the two-player version is more developed, but let's not
make it complicated! :). Hopefully it'll be worthing doing (I've had quite a
lot of people telling me how good it is - even in it's very *very* early
state! :). Oh, I've commented out some of the swearing! :)

There are a lot of comments in the code (remember, this code hasn't been
touched for a
_long time_!) which were Me <-> Bolty.

BB/TF     - this is me.
Bolty      - this is Bolty (doh!).

Neither of us can code games to save our sad manky little lives!

This game was originally aimed at users with an 020 processor and AGA.

Sorry if I've missed out anything important! Get in touch with me or something
on what to do next.

Bub-bye!

-- 
| A1200/28Mhz/2+4Mb/K56Flex/HyperCOM | Amiga Blitz 2 coder type UK bloke! |
| EMAIL: BootBlock@GeoCities.com     | www.geocities.com/SiliconValley/   |
| "NightLife BBS" - online soon!     | Lab/4868/index.html - almost ready |
`------------------------------------"------------------------------------'

