Content-Type: text/plain

On 15-Dec-97, Dave wrote:
>Hi there!

Hi,

>   I`ve got a problem with the ListView. I have been making a program
>   which has a GUI that remaps to the right colours if someone loads
>   a strange palette but while doing this there have been problems
>   in that some blitz commands ignore the colour numbers set in the
>   screens tags lists. So what should have been easy has turned into
>   a headache . 
>    Most of these commands I have found ways round or used a similar
>     commands which do what I want. But I still don`t know what to do
>    about the listview which has a black background, there for I can`t
>    see the Text, does anyone know how to alter the colours of a 
>    listview?    
>     There is a GTTAGs command with a colour tag but I couldn`t seem to
>     get it to change any colours.

I also had this problem when I was created the Foundation Prefs program. The
method I used was to create a Statement which would draw a rectangle (usually
colour 0) the width and height of the listview (or indeed any other gadget
which has this problem) at the listview's position *before* the listview is
attached. Then when the listview is attached to the window, the back is the
normal colour, allowing you to see again :)

Something like :

   Statement GTBack{x,y,width,height,col}
      ; I used the same numbers as where used in the ListView parameters for
the x,y, width and height then used                     ; some calculations
(trial and error here) to get it to position in the right place on the window,
cause for some                ; reason they appear to be different when using
WBox.
   
      WBox x+4,y+2,width-2,height-2,col      ; This is just an example (won't
be correct)
   End Statement

 - Daniel



@ENDNODE
