From: Alvaro Thompson <alvaro@enterprise.net>
Reply-To: alvaro@enterprise.net
To: Blitz-List <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Tue, 16 Dec 1997 07:20:51 -0000
Message-ID: <yam7289.2561.2015745680@mail.enterprise.net>
X-Mailer: YAM 1.3.5 [020] - Amiga Mailer by Marcel Beck
Organization: Team Mango
Subject: Microsoft? Ewwwwwww
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain


Hi guys!

This is probably a bit unrelated (again!), but I'll go ahead with it anyway:

I went up to the Isle of Wight (Where I live, unfortunately!) College
Information Evening last night. I am at the final stages of finishing my GCSEs
at the moment. I still don't know whether to go to College, or stay in the
Sixth Form, but I went along anyway, just to find out a little bit more about
it.

I specifically went to find out a bit more information about the IT related
courses that they run. The one I had in mind is a BTEC National Diploma
(Advanced 2 year course), and so I went along... had this long speech from
this guy (there were quite a few people in the room), and after 45 bloody
minutes (arghhhh.... seemed like a school lesson! ;), we finally had the
chance to go to the specific areas of our interest (eg Computing for my case).
So they took us to the IT Department, and when me and my mum got there, I
started to have a talk with the head of the department.

I was rather, shall I say, "scared" above all. I don't mean by the guy (well,
sort of, he was a bit of an asshole), but rather by his attitude. This guy
seemed to think that Microsoft products are the way to the future, and that
their products are really great!!! I was thinking to myself at that moment
"Mmmmmm......... My ass". We then went onto the subject of programming, and I
told him that I did a fair bit of programming at home, as a hobby, and also
HTML and crap. He then told me that in the BTEC course, we would be learning
Visual Basic! I then sort of dropped a sarcastic comment like "Mmmm.........
Visual Basic.... GRRRRRRRREAT". I told him that what I really wanted to learn
was more Java, Javascript, and C stuff, and then he came out with this speech
"Yes, we used to teach all these things, Java, Javascript, C, Pascal, all of
that! but the 'in' thing now is Visual Basic, all the great applications like
MS-Excell are written in it". This was most distressing. GREAT APPLICATION???
wtf is this guy on? What I really didn't like also, was the fact that he said
that they did Visual Basic because it was the "in" thing. Does this mean that,
I do the course, finish 2 years later, and then find out that there is a new
"in" programming language, and then all my knowledge I've learned at the
College is useless? Well, don't like the sound of that myself!

I then told him that me and a few friends were going over to Portsmouth
University between the 26th and the 30th, to learn a bit more about Java, and
Javascript (As part of us being Webmasters at school, we get this kinda stuff!
and btw....... bit of free advertising: www.rydehigh.iow.sch.uk). This guy
then started questioning WHY I was doing this, what the point of doing so
was... so I just told him that it was to broaden my knowledge in HTML and
stuff. He then look at me and said "ahhhhh", with this expression on his face
as if to say "bah, pointless".

Sorry if I mailed this LONG mail to the list (my apologies if anyone thinks
this is unnecessary), but I just wondered what everyone thinks about the
current Coding languages situation, and what did everyone think of this guy's
attitude???

cheers dudes

-- 

