<deletia>

With your experience in basic you should be able to code in a piss easy
language
like VB in a matter of weeks. You would be much better off doing A levels in
maths and business studies. Do not trust this man, the fact that he was trying
to intimidate you means that he knows that this course is rubbish.

>Sorry if I mailed this LONG mail to the list (my apologies if anyone thinks
>this is unnecessary), but I just wondered what everyone thinks about the
>current Coding languages situation, and what did everyone think of this guy's
