I like Borland C++, but work mainly with a 4GL for UNIX. Like it or not
Visual Basic will be with us for a while because it makes it very easy to
write large effective applications in a short amount of time. With the PC
standard approaching 300MHz PentiumII computers with 64meg of memory, the
slow bulky code will become harder to spot. The companies who order VB 
software do not care and will never care how cool the code is, they only
look at the price tag and the end result. The same goes for java, or J++
as it will soon be know.

By the way, will you guys stop pissing me off. VB is NOT a 4GL and never
will be:)

Thanks for reading my rant;)
