 Hi again,

I made one small mistake, in the last mail.
When you convert a C tag into a blitz
basic constant you should do like this.
(You should still use the 8 last digits
of the 10 given in the .h file).

 IN C

   #define MUIA_ThisIsATest 0x901a238d

 IN BLITZ

   #MUIA_ThisIsATest=3D$901a238d

In my last mail I forgot the $ sign infont
of the value (Needed since the value is
hexadecimal)

I have also tired to use a custom class
myself, and it worked. The one I tried was
HTMLtext.mcc I will adapt the whole tag
file, and e-mail me if you want it, along
with a small example on how to use it.

 ByE

-- =

