Received: (qmail 19352 invoked from network); 5 Dec 1997 18:34:00 -0000
Received: from seralph10.essex.ac.uk (155.245.240.160)
  by orca.ucd.ie with SMTP; 5 Dec 1997 18:34:00 -0000
Received: from fpgapc16.essex.ac.uk by seralph10.essex.ac.uk; (5.65v3.2/1.1.8.2/14Feb95-1154AM)
	id AA17356; Fri, 5 Dec 1997 18:33:48 GMT
From: C Dimitrakakis <cdimita@essex.ac.uk>
To: BlitzList <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Subject: Mysterious Bug Solved [related to Blizzard1230IV?]
Message-Id: <SIMEON.9712051831.A@fpgapc16.essex.ac.uk>
Date: Fri, 5 Dec 1997 18:34:31 +0000 (GMT)
Priority: NORMAL
X-Mailer: Simeon for Win32 Version 4.1.2 Build (32)
X-Authentication: IMSP
Mime-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: TEXT/PLAIN; CHARSET=US-ASCII

OK.. I had this strange bug...
Using a small 1-bitplane bitmap to draw lines onto
and then pass the data using Point() to an array(x,y)
I sometimes had lost lines, etc. (similar to The GETSHAPE problem)

On a message on the list it said that the last blit command runs in 
parallel with program code.. so I guess that this, in conjuction with 
Data Pre-Fetching when data cache Burst mode is turned on, might be the 
problem.

Anyway, doing:

Gosub draw_on_bitmap
VWait
Gosub read_bitmap_in_array

fixes the problem (the VWait is the fix)

You can use WaitBlitter_() alternatively I guess...


Christos Dimitrakakis (aka Olethros)
Electronic Engineer,
Software Developer for the Amiga computer
University of Essex




@ENDNODE
