On 05-Dec-97, C Dimitrakakis wrote:
>OK.. I had this strange bug...
>Using a small 1-bitplane bitmap to draw lines onto
>and then pass the data using Point() to an array(x,y)
>I sometimes had lost lines, etc. (similar to The GETSHAPE problem)

>On a message on the list it said that the last blit command runs in =

>parallel with program code.. so I guess that this, in conjuction with =

>Data Pre-Fetching when data cache Burst mode is turned on, might be the =

>problem.

>Anyway, doing:

>Gosub draw_on_bitmap
>VWait
>Gosub read_bitmap_in_array

>fixes the problem (the VWait is the fix)

>You can use WaitBlitter_() alternatively I guess...


Yes it is the problem, and the cure is the waitblitter_
(or vwait in your case because the blit is so short).


