On Mon, 8 Dec 1997 17:50:36 GMT Mike Carter 
<57229007%mmu.ac.uk@uk.ac.essex.mailhost> wrote:

> > Mike Carter wrote:
> > > What does NULL actually equal?  Is it just a zero?? 
Yes :) Zero:)
If you call a system function that returns null if it failed, you test 
for NULL in C, and for 0 in basic... oh.
The test is basically
if (function())
	do this
else
	oops, it failed, do that
endif

which tests for a non-zero value.




Christos Dimitrakakis (aka Olethros)
