On 10 Dec 97 at 19:26, C Dimitrakakis spewed forth:

> Shifting, multiplying and dividing operators have to work differently 
> on signed/unsigned numbers.

 There are also different versions of the branch instructions that 
take into account signed or unsigned, i.e 11111111 > 01111111 for 
unsigned numbers but 11111111 < 01111111 for signed numbers.


