Content-Type: text/plain

Hi,

> All operating systems are written at least partially in machine code.  On a
> machine such as the Amiga, it would be beneficial to have the whole thing
> written in assembler.  Assembler provides the ultimate speed. 

Writing a whole OS in 68k Asm is just as bad as writing it in Blitz.
Of course some important functions should be in Asm but I'm sure you'll
find modern OS are written in a portable language.

The best advice for someone who wants to write an OS is take a look
through the RKRM's for AmigaOS and see if you think you can do
better :) If all you want to do is create an Environment that sits
on top of an existing OS (something like Dopus Magellan) then it's
probably the best way to go. The problem is, once you've got this
thing up to a good standard we'll have Amiga OS4 out :)

Cheers,

Paul


