On 20-Dec-97, Paul Burkey wrote:
 
>> All operating systems are written at least partially in machine code.

>On a
>> machine such as the Amiga, it would be beneficial to have the whole
>thing
>> written in assembler.  Assembler provides the ultimate speed. 
 
  Something to consider is will the assembler be used on a PPC based
machine? If so you may want to keep the assem PPC compatible- check out
some PPC assembler docs.

-- 
      Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
     



@ENDNODE
