On 20/12/97, Christos wrote:
>On Sat 20 Dec 1997, Anton wrote: 
>> On 20-Dec-97, Sami wrote:
>>  
>> >> OSes are written in Assembler ...
>> >I got you a suprise!! Amiga OS is written in C !!!
>I Thought it was written in B:)

Just for your info,
AmigaOS was first written in BCPL and MC68000 assembler.

The Exec part was written by Carl (REBOL) Sassenrath
(most probably in assembler). 

The DOS part was a port/adaptation of TripOS by the Amiga people
(most probably in BCPL).
(
The original TripOS was made by Metacomco I think
(this may be a legend, but I read it in books and magazines),
they were famous for making compilers by that time
)

Some other parts may have been in C from the begining,
graphics.library for instance,
some others in assembler, clist.library for instance.

>From version to version, the BCPL parts were ported to C,
you can see it, because of the different way of using strings.

I guess that the whole OS is now BCPL free and that the innermost loops
and things that should be as quick as possible are in assembler.


-- Philippe Socias ----------------------------------------
At Work: psocias@microresearch.be     Tel: + 32 2 734 98 18
Private: philippe_socias@hotmail.com  Tel: + 32 81 74 64 39



@ENDNODE
