Hi Alvaro,

On 27-Dec-97, Alvaro Thompson wrote:

>Heys!

>I was wondering.... Does anyone now if there is any way in which you can tell
>how many colours a palette contains? 'cause I wanna do a little tool, wich
>will load a palette, and will then convert the colours of the palette into
>source code for Blitz. However, I need to know how many colours the palette
>file conatains.

>Any ideas?

There must be a way to read this from the palette's header (I am assuming you
are using just palettes, it's easy to get this info from a pic or a brush),
but I don't know how to get it from just a palette.

However, you could initialize a palette object to full depth first, then load
your palette into this and see how many colours have been changed.  This would
fail of course if the last colour in the palette you load is black, but still
should be good enough - if more than the first 16 colours were changed from
black, of course you have a 32 colour palette, etc.

And have a Happy New Year!
-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
