> I was wondering.... Does anyone now if there is any way in which you
> can tell how many colours a palette contains? 'cause I wanna do a little
> tool, wich will load a palette, and will then convert the colours of the
> palette into source code for Blitz. However, I need to know how many
> colours the palette file conatains.
> Any ideas?

   Sure... back when I was planning on doing commercial game
   development in BLITZ, I created some custom palette-routines... one
   of these is a procedure which loads the palette from either an IFF
   picture, brush or palette file.

   I'll have a look in hard-drive later tonight and either send you a
   little procedure to extract the number of colors or else I'll just send
   you the paletteload procedure... okay?

   The full palette-system might be useful to other BLITZ-programmers, so
   maybe I'll put them on my BLITZ-page.  They allow fading to a color,
   fading to a palette, adjusting the brightness of a palette, tinting a
   palette, color-cycling and I can't remember what else...


