On Sun, 07 Dec 1997 22:16:31 +0000 Dave 
<d.boaz%virgin.net@uk.ac.essex.mailhost> wrote:

> Hello  blitzers,
> 
>                 I have recently been looking on the devCD about parsing iff`s.
>    Before I looked this up I thought I knew how to do this but the info a found
>    has got me confused. Does anyone have any source code for doing this using the
>    OS functions. Really I want to identify what type of file it is , Brush ,
>    Animbrush , picture .

Hm... You want to use IffParse? You have to *know* what the file is.. 
then use IffParse(...."8SVX".....) and it looks at the file and sees if 
it is an 8SVX..

In order to know if a file is 8SVX, I guess you could do it by reading 
the file.. it should go something like that

..somedatahere.....IFFxxxx.....DATA...

when you find IFF (i think it terminates with chr$(0)).. the string 
after that (terminating with a 0 again, I think, maybe) is the type of 
the IFF
so it will be 
IFF8SVX for sound, IFFILBM for iff picture/brush.. etc.
then you can use IffParse to look at it.

By coincidence, I made some code that loads a sound using IffParse 
yesterday- might help - but I did it only using the iffparse.h autodoc, 
so I am not sure if it is 100% correct. (I left my CDs in greece.. )



Christos Dimitrakakis (aka Olethros)
Electronic Engineer,
Software Developer for the Amiga computer
University of Essex




