Organization: Electrus Software
Subject: Re: PROGDIR
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

On 04-Dec-97, Tim Johnson wrote:

Hi there :-)

>I put: 

>OpenFile 0,"PROGDIR:Hopeless.config"

>in my program, and when executed, up popped a requester asking for me
>to insert volume PROGDIR:.  How can I find the name of the current
>directory in Blitz?

As somebody else wrote (Mike?) it will work okay when the code is actually
compiled into an Executable but there is another method of finding the path.

Use this at the start of your program:

; ==========================================================

MaxLen path$=200

NameFromLock_ GetProgramDir_(),&path$,200
path$=Peek$(&path$)

If Right$(path$,1)=":"
Else
path$=path$+"/"
Endif

; ==========================================================

And then just change your OpenFile command to :

OpenFile 0,path$+"HopeLess.config"

Hope this helps!

Byyyee!,

David Hodge/Electrus Software



@ENDNODE
