Hi,

On Wed, 03 Dec 1997 20:21:49 -0600, trilobyte@rockford.com wrote:

> OpenFile 0,"PROGDIR:Hopeless.config"
> 
> in my program, and when executed, up popped a requester asking for me
> to insert volume PROGDIR:.  How can I find the name of the current
> directory in Blitz?

You can use "PROGDIR:", as you did above, that works in the
executable, but not in the editor.

I solve this by useing a base path variable in the begining of my
program containing the absolute path of my program, when the program
is finished I change it to "PROGDIR:" and do the final compilation.


--

