On 05-Dec-97, Allan Pedersen wrote:
>Davs!

>I just started working with tooltypes in Player!

>When i compile it i call it PinkPlay. But if somebody have 2 versions of it
>they might wanna call the first PinkPlay0_8 and the second PinkPlay0_9! And
>then when i try to find pinkPlay.info i wount find it :(

>So what i would like to know is that. How do i get the .Exe filename?

Theres a command supplied with the Blitz Support Suite, but if you
don't have it (like me) just place this at the start of your program:

programname$=taskname$(0)

programname$ will now contain the name of .exe :-), if you need to find
the current programdir (not using PROGDIR:) then mail me :-)

Byyeee!,

-- 

