X-Mailer: YAM 1.3.4 [040] - Amiga Mailer by Marcel Beck
Subject: Re: PubScreens
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

On 29-Nov-97, Alexander Wingrove wrote:
AW>How can I find out if the front-most screen is a PubScreen? and if it
AW>is, what it's PubScreen name is?

I hate to answer my own post, but I have figured out the answer. The
following shows how ( requires Amigalibs.res ):

--8<-------------------------------------------

FindScreen 0
*scr.Screen = Peek.l(Addr Screen(0))
scr_type.l  = *scr\Flags AND #SCREENTYPE
If NOT (scr_type =  #PUBLICSCREEN OR scr_type = #WBENCHSCREEN)
  WbToScreen 0
  *scr = Peek.l(Addr Screen(0))
EndIf

--8<-------------------------------------------

*scr now points at the frontmost screen if it is a Pub Screen, else it
points at workbench.

( Isn't it amazing what you come across when reading the developer CD for
a bit :)

Bye,
Alex

-- 
+-- Alex Wingrove / awingrove@thenet.co.uk --+

[      www.thenet.co.uk/~awingrove/blitz/       ]
[ Blitz Program Collection  and  Blitz List FAQ ]



@ENDNODE
