>Anton Reinauer wrote:

>> - You'll just have to run your game in Amiga or QAmiga mode- with
>faster
>> processors the CPU overhead from multi-tasking in negligible.

> Does anyone know what the difference is between Amiga and QAmiga mode?
> I thought you were only able to use QAmiga for temporary file access
> acording to the manual.

  Theoretically it's only for file access, but a cunning bugger by the
name of Bruce Webster decided to try it for gaming purposes. I seem to
remember vaguely something about Acid improving QAmiga mode early on
from just displaying a bitmap while you did file access, to allowing you
to do blitting and other things in QAmiga.

-- 
