> I have this problem with reading and/or writing to a file!!
> 
> Okey here goes:
> 
> 1. I get my Window's X and Y cords
> 2. I OpenFile 1 where i want to store the cords in!
> 3. I set FileOutput 1
> 4. I then Nprint X and NPrint Y
> 5. I Closefile 1
> 
> BUT when i want to get the cords there is a problem!!
> 
> Lets say X=000
> 
> If i use x=Edit(3) and then NPrint "X=",X . It will print X=0 and not X=000
> 
> therefor i would like to know how i can read the first string (alias X) and
> the next string (alias Y).
> 
Rather than write the variable as a number to the file convert it to 
a string using STR$().  Before you use this though set the string 
format to three zeros using Format "000".  This will make it print 
three zeros even if the number is only two digits long.

Then write to the pile using NPrint Str$(X).

Cheerio,

Mike.
