Subject: Re: RTG support libs for BB2.1
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

Hi Budda/Progress,

>> I've seen your WWW page but i did not find any RTG or GFX-CARD lib
>> for Blitz Basic 2! Is there any? And where is it?

You can do it 3 ways.

a> Use graphics.library functions which are built into blitz. You'll
need to read up on the graphics.library and intuition.library functions
using the Amiga autodocs.

b> use fdconvert to convert the library of your GFX card system
to blitz. This will be the CyberGraphX library or the Picasso96
equivelent.

c> using fdconvert to convert the RTGMaster library to blitz and
use that.

All 3 methods have their advantages depending on what type of
project you're working on. I chose h first option for Foundation
because it's the easiest and it works for Picasso96 and CyberGraphX
automaticaly. RTGMaster is recomended if you want to make a
chunky based game like Doom or something that uses similar
rendering.

If there was a Blitz lib that supported GFX cards then it would have
to go for one of the 3 choices above and it would probably not be
any easier than using any of the above choices.

There's a fourth method and thats to use the compatable Blitz basic
functions like intuition windows, screens, and all functions that
render to windows and screens.

Cheers,

Paul

