X-mailer: Pegasus Mail for Windows (v2.53/R1)
Message-ID: <CDC18A78A1@qmwcc5.qmw.ac.uk>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="US-ASCII"

     Jake Frederick wrote:

> What is the fastest, easiest way to put an info bar to display score, lives,
> etc. over a Blitz mode screen?

The easiest way is to set up 2 coplists like this

initcoplist 0,44,10,$10004,8,16,-4
initcoplist 1,60,200,$10004,8,16,-4

displaybitmap 0,0
displaybitmap 1,1

createdisplay 0,1

This sets up bitmap 0 for the info bar and bitmap 1 for the main 
screen.  Try changing the sixty to a smaller value.. The value is 
worked by 44 + size of info bar (in this case 10) + 2 Blitz needs 
the 2 to reinitailize the copper

Regards
Steven



@ENDNODE
