In-Reply-To: <7E538A83B3A@EXCELSIOR.MMU.AC.UK>
X-Mailer: YAM 1.3.4 [040] - Amiga Mailer by Marcel Beck
Subject: Re: Screen Double Buffering ??
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

Hi Mike,

> > Just a plain and simple question - How the heck do you do double
> > buffering with a 'screen' in amiga mode ??
> > You know, a simple two bitmap swap for flicker free blitting.

> I think Paul Burkley said you open an intuition screen twice the 
> height and don't allow it to auto scroll.  Then just swap between the 
> first and second half of the screen and it wont have any flickering 
> because it's hardware move and not blitter job.

Thats right for CyberGraphX double buffering because it's the only
way to get two bitmaps on the GFX card at the same time. I don't
think there's any other way to reserve bitmaps in GFX card ram. In
Foundation I have a screen hat is 3 times the height for tripple
buffering! Only a GFX card will let you do hat sort of thing with
an 800x1800 screen! :)

As far as regular AGA coding goes you can use the ShowBitmap
command. It's not a very system friendly method but it does work
and I use hat for the AGA version of Foundation.

Cheers,

Paul

-- 
