> 
>   Tripple buffering ? How much extra speed would you get from this?
>
By tripple buffering he probably means using a 3rd buffer that only 
stores the background. This way you can use Qblit instead of bblit (you 
have to use the 2nd form of the Unqueue command). This is halfway 
between normal Qblit and bblit in speed.. - of course if you use custom 
blitting routines it can be even faster.

 
