Hi Dave,

> > In Foundation I have a screen that is 3 times the height for tripple
> > buffering! Only a GFX card will let you do that sort of thing with
> > an 800x1800 screen! :)

>   Tripple buffering ? How much extra speed would you get from this?

Well there are different ways of using the 3rd buffer and my system
uses the less common method. The third buffer contains the textured
floor. It's created by blitting over 300 diamond shapes pieces in an
Isometric landscape that has various height levels and various textures.
So it's better to calculate/render this once than to do it every frame.
For the AGA version this 3rd buffer is in Fast ram so the rendering is
very fast. The regular double buffers must be in chip mem because they
must be displayed.

Cheers,

Paul

