> Well that Triple buffering is only usefull, if you are doing game that is
> NOT synced to VBI. This because action type games can NOT run in
> different speed, it have to be smooth to be playable. So that's why it
> have to render the screen in one VBI and thou the extrabuffer is
> useless. In action game you could use 2.5 buffering thou. :)
> I mean keep your background in extra buffer and use it as
> background source in your blittings.

   Actually, games are what triple-buffering is most used for...

   The point is that the display is still being updated at 1Vbl, but you
   are gaining a bit more time to process code and draw gfx.  Another
   feature of the TB is that your program might drop to a fraction below
   1Vbl, say from 60fps(NTSC) to 58-59fps, with TB the display would
   still be synced at 1Vbl, rather than dropping back to 30fps...
 
   I can send you an example source I made, so you can see BLITZ 
   Triple-Buffering in action, if you like?


      Take  care,   
      GARFIELD
