X-Mailer: Pegasus Mail for Win32 (v2.54)
Message-Id: <E0xgSnm-00061s-00@mserv1a.u-net.net>

On 11 Dec 97 at 14:24, Garfield Benjamin spewed forth:

>    The point is that the display is still being updated at 1Vbl, but you
>    are gaining a bit more time to process code and draw gfx.  Another
>    feature of the TB is that your program might drop to a fraction below
>    1Vbl, say from 60fps(NTSC) to 58-59fps, with TB the display would
>    still be synced at 1Vbl, rather than dropping back to 30fps...

 But if the screen redraws are synched to an interrupt which occurs 
every VBL, then you will drop back to 30fps, if you use the example 
code that was posted a few msgs ago, because new frames are only 
shown once they are rendered, so if 1 frame goes over 1 VBL, then the 
next frame won't be shown until the end of the 2nd, effectively 
reducing your frame rate to 30fps.




Farewell, for now,

.oO David McMinn Oo.
-=-=-=-=-==-=-=-=-=-
*A1200T 1.3Gb 16xCD*
-=-=-=-=-==-=-=-=-=-


@ENDNODE
