Hi Andreas,

> And I managed to make most of the things to  work
> by using the screentags, but I cant find any tags
> to disable the screen depth  gadget  (The  screen
> gadget  in the upper right corner, which lets you
> bring another screen infront of the current one),
> and how to turn of the titlebar.

Doesn't the #SA_ShowTitle tag remove this? Without the titlebar
I wouln't expect there to be a depth gadget.

> I tried using the #SA_ShowTitle tag  to  turn  of
> the  titlebar,  but  it  didn't  work.

It seems to work for me okay. I'm using a totaly plain screen
with no gadets, no dragging, no nothing :) This is the taglist
I'm using:

#SA_Width,ScrW
#SA_Height,FullH
#SA_DisplayID,id
#SA_Depth,8
#SA_ShowTitle,False
#SA_Exclusive,True
#TAG_DONE,0

Exclusive is similar to no drag but it has the added benefit of
not allowing people to drag other screens to reveal this one.
Basicly it is impossible for my screen to be shown togethr with
any other screen at the same time.

> Does anyone know how  to  slove  these  last  two
> problems I have? I open a borderless window on my
> screen, and I can solve the problem with  turning
> of  the  titlebar,  by  using  the windowtag that
> traps right mouse button presses  (cant  remember
> what  it's called, but it has the value $100000),
> but that still leaves me with  the  screen  depth
> gadget  problem,  and I whould like to solve both
> of these things with screen tags if possible, and
> not have to use the windowtag.

Menus are attached to windows and not screens. if you want to turn
them off you have to turn them off when you open the window. I
don't think theres a screens tag that will alter the modes of any
windows that open. Maybe the "Menus Off" command would do that for
you.

Cheers,

Paul



