Subject: SDK Conversions
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

I've been converting some SDK's (Software Developer's Kit) to Blitz (eg.
XFDMaster, DayDream BBS, VirtualMem, etc) and I've come across a couple of
things ....

1. What's a "APTR" ?  I can only guess and say that it's a string pointer
("*") - ie.

   APTR SomeData      --->   *SomeData       (is this right?)

2. What do I do with the following ? :

   #XFDPFF_ADDR (1<<XFDPFB_ADDR)

What's this do? Bit-shifting the variable/constant? How do I convert to "Blitz
format"?

Mega thanks in advance!

-- 
