On 24 Dec 97 at 1:06, Joseph Cox spewed forth:

> I've been converting some SDK's (Software Developer's Kit) to Blitz (eg.
> XFDMaster, DayDream BBS, VirtualMem, etc) and I've come across a couple of
> things ....
> 
> 1. What's a "APTR" ?  I can only guess and say that it's a string pointer
> ("*") - ie.
> 
    APTR SomeData      --->   *SomeData       (is this right?)

Yes, but it doesn't point to a string, I think it's like a void 
pointer (in C), i.e. it doesn't point to anything specific. Just do a 
DEFTYPE.b *SomeData in blitz.

> 2. What do I do with the following ? :
> 
>    #XFDPFF_ADDR (1<<XFDPFB_ADDR)

 Thats some weird-ass code, even for C. Do you mean:
#define XFDPFF_ADDR (1<<XFDPFB_ADDR)

If you do, then this is the blitz code:
#XFDPFF_ADDR = 1 ASL #XFDPFB_ADDR

thats assuming that the XFDPFB_ADDR is a constant as well.


Farewell, for now,

-=-=-=-=-==-=-=-=-=-
*A1200T 1.3Gb 16xCD*
-=-=-=-=-==-=-=-=-=-



