On 03-Dec-97, Wright J.A wrote:

Sory don't now almost anything from the sound commands. :(

>   Also, i want to write a 3d polygon space sim for 030+ machines... am
>i right in saying that the Polyf function uses the blitter, and it is
>faster to use the CPU to draw the polygons???  i say this because i have=

>a 3d demo in Blitz, and it`s only just managing to draw one ship,
>whereas in things like Frontier it can have many ships.... so does would=

>Frontier use the Blitter or use the CPU????

Well the frontier most likely is using just the blitter. BUT it will
calculate new lines while the blitting is done. and after the blit is
finished an interrupt handler then writes next blit to the blitter.
With this way you can draw a whole lot more polygons than using normal
blitting commands from blitz. Disavantage is that you have to write your
own blitting routines... And that can be pain in the a**!

I'm writing such code in asm and I think it could be translated as series=

of statements or functions... but the statement handling in the midle is
quite slow so it would be better way of doing it in big asm statement.
So you would need a big punch of asm coding skill to do that.

OH and almost forget to say. Using CPU to clear the bitmap witch was just=

shown while the blitter is still drawing to the other could speed things =
up
framatically.

>keep on Blitzing........ and in 3D application some Asm wouldn't hurt ei=
ther.

