Content-Type: text/plain

Hi,

On 02-Dec-97, Wright J.A wrote:
>Right,  
>   how do u use the SetPeriod command???? when i press help over it it
>tells me that the syntax for it is : 

>                      SetPeriod  sound#,period

>However when i tried SetPeriod 0,500  i get an error saying that i have
>given an incorrect ChannelMask.  I then tried SetPeriod 0,1  : which
>gave no errors, but it`s changind sound 0, channelmask 1, but theres
>no-where to actually change the period!!!!  whats going on??????

You are using the command correctly (the 500 or so, at a period of 1 the sound
will play so quick you won't hear it) - there is a bug in the debugger!
Try this:


snd$=(any iff sound)
LoadSound 0,snd$           ;load a sound  for testing
again                      ;start here
Sound 0,15                 ;play the sound
Print "Enter pitch : "     ;just a slight prompt
a=Edit(8)                  ;get user's input in a crude way
If a <1 Then End           ;if it is 0, we're outta here!
;----------------------------------------------------------------
Runerrsoff                 ;tell the debugger to not check this
;----------------------------------------------------------------
SetPeriod 0,a              ;set the new pitch
;----------------------------------------------------------------
Runerrson                  ;ok, we can use the debugger again
;----------------------------------------------------------------
Goto again                 ;and go play it again

Of course, you will need to remove the runerrs commands when you compile the
finished exec.

-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
