Yeah, well I have a similar problem with Wreckage.
Translating the 3D rotation and projection to one 162-byte asm (which 
fits in 68030 instruction cache) statement make a BIG difference ... 
the frame rate getting from a measly 16fps to almost 50.
I will most probably make these routines publicly available for people 
to use :) (I've just started making some that are even faster..)



Christos Dimitrakakis (aka Olethros)
