On Thu, 4 Dec 1997 17:05:58 +1300 Julian Kinraid 
<jkinraid%clear.net.nz@uk.ac.essex.mailhost> wrote:


> I haven't used it myself, but I would assume you just -
> 
> bin:  INCBIN "data/code.bin"
> 
This works perfectly well for my 3d asm routines.
If you have somethin like a C2p or a 3d routine, and all the loop is in 
asm.. then GetReg is only executed once, so it doesn't really matter :)

> and just jump to bin: to execute that code.
> 
> > This because I could take some move16 to my C2P code too!!
> > And in some cases the FPU commands could be really big help!!
> 
> If you're interested I've written a program that lets you type in an instruction, eg. mulu.l d0,d1:d2, and it will give you the data for that command back, eg. DC.w $47c5.   It uses PhxAss, so any command that PhxAss supports can be used, except using labels.  I have an idea on how to use labels, but I don't know whether it's worthwile adding it.  It would let you use commands like -
> jmp ([tabel,pc],d0.w*4)
> 
> I could develop it further, but I don't know if I have time or whether it's worth it, but you can have it anyway :)
>
Nah, better use PhxAss on its own.
and that double-indexed addressing is pretty slow, so don't use it :)
Also, long mulu/s are slow (twice as slow as .w ones)!
Furthermore the 68060 does not support the MUL.l 32,32->64 format 
(mulu.l dx,dy:dz) so *never* use it, unless you make seperate 060 
version.




> Ciao,
> Julian Kinraid
> 

Christos Dimitrakakis (aka Olethros)
Electronic Engineer,
Software Developer for the Amiga computer
University of Essex




