Here's my question from friday again - hope someone ca help...

Hi Blitzers!

Could someone of you explain, you I can set the font of titlebars of wind=
ows
and screens? Look at the following part of my source (not executable):

  scrtag.taglist\a\a=3D#LikeWorkbench,False
  scrtag.taglist\b\a=3D#Width,\wi
  ...  <setting tags>
  scrtag.taglist\l\a=3D#SysFont,0
  ...
  Use IntuiFont 0
  scree.l=3DOpenScreenTagList_(False,&scrtag\a\a)
  ScreenToFront_(&scree)
  FindScreen 0,Scr
  Use Screen 0

I'm loading the font into the program and setting it with <Use Intuifont>=
 to
number 0.
This has the result that all gadgets in the windows are using the loaded =
font.
But the font of the titlebars (windows and also the screen) are using alw=
ays
Topaz 8.

I thought that I must set the parametre #SysFont in the screentaglist to
another number. For instance I load the font to number 1 and use
<scrtag.taglist\l\a=3D#SysFont,1> but it doesn't work...

I have this problem since I'm using <OpenScreenTagList_> to open the scre=
en
(for gfx card compatibility).

Could someone help?

Thanks in advance.

Andre

