Subject: SetWindowPointerA_
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

Hi All,

I am using the command SetWindowPointerA_ with a small tag list to set and
unset the system busy pointer while my program is busy.

But since this command is for v39 only (Wb 3+), I have two questions:

What happens if the program is run on Wb 2.xx?  A crash, or does it just do
nothing?

And, is there a way to do this on Wb 2.xx?  I have tried the RTlockWindow, but
I can only get this to work on one window at a time.  I need to do this to 2
or 3 windows at once.

Thanks for your help.
-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
