> And, is there a way to do this on Wb 2.xx?  I have tried the RTlockWindow, but
> I can only get this to work on one window at a time.  I need to do this to 2
> or 3 windows at once.

I have got RTLockWindow to work on multiple windows.  All you have to 
do is create an array and hold the pointer returned adfter calling 
the lockwindow command for each window.  This can be done in a FOR 
... NEXT loop.  I can't remember the correct syntax for the command 
but I think you just put the window number in brackets...

lock.l(1)=RTLockWindow(1)
lock.l(2)=RTLockWindow(2)

... of do you have to do a Use Window before locking each window?  
Hmmm... I can't remember but IT DOES WORK as I use it in my 
encyclopedia engine.

Cheerio,


Mike.
