Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="------------C5B32DA11C2"

This is a multi-part message in MIME format.

--------------C5B32DA11C2
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=us-ascii
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Curt Esser wrote:

> And, is there a way to do this on Wb 2.xx?  I have tried the RTlockWindow, but
> I can only get this to work on one window at a time.  I need to do this to 2
> or 3 windows at once.

  Here are some code statements for you.
   The first Locks all windows apart from the window those number you pass to
   the statement.
   The second statement Unlocks all windows that are locked.

OK

DAVE

--------------C5B32DA11C2
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=us-ascii
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit
Content-Disposition: inline; filename="Lockwin"

Dim WinLock.l(Maximum Window-1)

Statement LockWindows{wn}       ; wn = window number NOT to be locked
SHARED WinLock()
  For a=0 To Maximum Window-1
    If a<>wn
      If Peek.l(Addr Window(a))<>0
          WinLock(a)=RTLockWindow(a)
      End If
    End If
  Next
End Statement

Statement UnLockWindows{}       ; Unlocks all windows that are locked
SHARED WinLock()
  For a=0 To Maximum Window-1
    If WinLock(a)<>0 Then RTUnlockWindow a,WinLock(a)
  Next
End Statement

--------------C5B32DA11C2--



@ENDNODE
