> 
I'm having the same problem and so is my flat mate!  I don't 
understand the stupidity of it !?!

Anyway I learnt in class (I actually learnt something at Uni!) last 
week that the last BIT of the BYTE holds the sign value.

%10000011  = -3
 ^
This BIT, when 1, means the value is a negative (or is it the other 
way around).

Hope this helps and maybe you can work out a way of using this.  
Sorry I couldn't be more exact but I've got to rush through all my 
e-mails before next lesson.

bbyyyyyeee

Mike.

