Well this is VERY VERY irritating thing that I found.

So lets start:

Everybody knows the compiler directive AMIGA,
but if you would want to use utility.libraries amiga2date command!!!

You just can't because blitz is making the amiga part as an compiler
directive. You can use names and functions which starts with the amiga, b=
ut
the next character CAN'T BE NUMERICAL!!!

So because this really is frustrating. I thougth, that if somebody knows =
how
to change the name of the utility.library function (the blitz token I mea=
n).
Could you make it to the utility.library1 file or just tell me what to do=
=2E

Or is this even possible?

PS. Token changing tool could be cool too!!

