X-Mailer: Microsoft Internet Mail 4.70.1155
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

> Im wanna use sprites in my game (up to 2 at the same time), they
> will be >32 pxls wide and have 15 colours (maximum of 2 sprites
> then i guess). 

   Actually, AGA sprites can be up to 64 pixels pixel wide, although
   you still need to combine two sprites for 15-color images...


> The problem is i cant get the colour nor their display to work good.

   If you are trying to use sprites along with the AGA Dual-Playfield
   mode... then you'll have used that DisplayControls statement I listed.
   That has remapped Dual-Playfield colours to use colour-registers
    0-15 & 16-31 and it has ALSO remapped the sprite colors from 
   registers 16-31 to 240-255 (if I remember correctly)... sorry about
   that, I should have mentioned this along with the previous
   DisplayControls info...

   Anyway, try copying your sprite palette into registers 240-255 and
   see if that doesn't do the trick.


> No slices will be used, instead display.library with displaysprite, the
> coplist is as shows:
> initcoplist 0,44,256,$x3414,8,yyy,0
> x = is it required to have "$1" there and must i also set yyy=256?
> that is the way in the example with blitz, but im not gonna use that
> many colours...

   Well, you could compute it in binary or decimal, but leaving it as
   hex-notation (with the $) looks pretty clear to me. 

   If you are using the AGA Dual-Playfield mode (and sprites) then you
   should set numcolors to 256.  You might only be showing 32 or
   48 colours, but internally you have changed the palette-layout and 
   the sprites will actually be using the last 16 colours (240-255).

   
> what about displayadjusts and displaycontrols?

   You need DisplayControls for reasons explained in the last reply.

   You may need to reduce the width of the display using Display
   Adjust... if you have trouble with your display being broken then
   you're probably overloading the puny AGA-bandwith limits, so try
   reducing the displaywidth to compensate for this...


      Take  care,   
      GARFIELD
      _________________________
      Current projects...
      SideShooter(AMOS): 98% Complete
      Website(http://www.sosbbs.com/~gbenjam): 25% Complete


@ENDNODE
