Subject: Re: Sprites, DualPF etc =)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=iso-8859-1
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable


 Hiya Peter,

I have had a look at Gloom 3, and you are right
it's been written  in Blitz Basic. I  know  the
guy that has  made it, he  is a  good friend of
mine. He's not Italian, he's  actually English,
and his name is  Gareth Murfin. But  sayig that
Gloom 3 was  written  completly  in blitz isn't
true. =


He  actually  got  the rights  to use  the real
Gloom engine used in  the  other two games, and
is written in ASM, and thats  why he is able to
get so good speed, when  using chunky to planar
graphics from blitz. So  his blitz  source  has
the 3D  engine  as Statement(s) and callas them
to update the graphics.

Blitz just dont have the  speed  needed  to  do
that kind of stuff, and thats  to bad. I  guess
somekind of 3D lib  chould  be  written to take
care  of  the c2p  stuff, but  I havn't  really
looked into this myself. =


On aminet you can  find  an  attempt  to make a
Doom style game from blitz. I think the archive
is called Doom4BB2 (Doom  For  Blitz  Basic 2),
and can be found in  dev/basic. I think it uses
some  c2p lib  or  something like that. I think
a  simple c2p lib   has  been   written, but  I
heard   is   was  hard to  use, and   full   of
limitations and bugs. =


Hope this helps. ByE!

-- =

