Hi,

On 17-Dec-97, Daniel Allsopp wrote:
>Hi,
>   Does anyone know how to stop a sound from playing, after it's started
>playing using the Sound command??

>My program starts playing a sound at a specific event, the sound is quite
>long, so it starts playing again (with the next event) before the end of the
>sample is reached, stopping the previous sound, and starting again.

>When all the events have finished, I fade the sound out using the volume
>command. But when I return the sound to full ; Volume 15,64,64,64,64 

>the sound is still playing. How do I stop it??

The easiest way is to create a blank sound object (with nothing in it) and
play this on the same channel(s) as the sound you want to stop.

Bye...


