game in BLITZ mode, that can be played across the internet, using TCP/IP
or whatever... i expect this to be a no!!!!  therefore i might take time
(probably a LOT of time) to try and write some code for this purpose....
only trouble is i haven`t got a where to start, apart from i was told
that it can`t be done, because you have got to recieve incoming packets
and deal with them straight away....  but i thought of just using an
interupt to deal with them.......
 
    Any ideas or help would be appreciated, as once a single person has
written this code, it couls be used in everyone`s Blitz games, and then
we could see a real surge of internet games for Amiga (something which i
feel is currently lacking)!

Thanks,
   James


