Organization: Team Mango
Subject: TED Lives!
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain


hullo Blitzers!

I imagine that by now, everyone uses the latest (or fairly latest) version of
SuperTED. Well, I must say that I've always prefered the original Blitz Ted. I
did try using SuperTED for quite a while, but I simply couldn't stand it.

The basic thing I couldn't stand.. is. well......... it looks to "Intuition"
orientated. By this I mean, it looked to WB2+, unlike good old Ted. Don't get
me wrong, it's not that I think WB2+ is crap, in fact, I think Wb3 rules, and
I do like making OS2+ stuff. The thing I've always thought is that blitz is
separated from other languages because of its unique editor. Ted had the
rainbows, and it looked 1.3, which for once, just once, I really liked.

It's a shame that it moved on to SuperTED, 'cause that meant that no more
development was done on Ted :( Shame really, 'cause I still, and always will,
use Ted. I wish someone would implement all the stuff that SuperTed had, but
with the look and feel of the original Ted.

Anyway, this is just my view.... what do others think?

-- 

