On Fri, 05 Dec 1997 22:30:02 -0000 Alvaro Thompson 
<alvaro%enterprise.net@uk.ac.essex.mailhost> wrote:

> 
> I know i've been going on for ages to find out how to do this......... but I
> really need answered......
> 
> Me and Gareth are still trying to get this MUD server to work. Our problem at
> the moment is:
> 
> How do we determine which user can be sent what message. By this we mean that
> we need to know how to send ONE particular message to ONE particular user.
> Unfortunately, Paul Burkey's TCP examples show you how to send message to ALL
> users, not just one user.
> 
Case 1)If you want to  send a message from server to user,
send it to their IP address!

Case 2)If you want to send a message from user to user,
send message to server, using high-level headers (ie, raw ascii user 
input). The server, after some time, will send the message as described 
in case 1)

BTW, I'm experimenting with some abstract networking protocols, writing 
some functions in Blitz.. if anyone wants them :)


Christos Dimitrakakis (aka Olethros)
Electronic Engineer,
Software Developer for the Amiga computer
University of Essex




@ENDNODE
