From: Alexander Wingrove <awingrove@thenet.co.uk>
Reply-To: awingrove@thenet.co.uk
To: Blitz List <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Sun, 07 Dec 1997 21:37:22 -0000
Message-ID: <yam7280.1123.30439160@smtp.thenet.co.uk>
X-Mailer: YAM 1.3.4 [040] - Amiga Mailer by Marcel Beck
Subject: Testers Please
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

Hi,

I have finished my first program that I would like to upload to Aminet.
It is called HandBook and it is a commodity that displays a popup window
showing, for example, all your .doc and .guide files in HELP:.

Before I upload it though, I would like some other people to test it and
make sure I haven't made any silly mistakes.

If you test it, I'll send you full source code as well which shows how to
do things like:

Use Triton in Blitz
Use RICommodities lib
Use RIApp lib
Give your program an ARexx port
Recurse through directories searching for files
Use the MatchPattern_ OS command
Read and write file comments
Open on the front-most public screen

The source code will also be on my web site once the program has been
tested.

So if you want to test HandBook, email me ( not the list ) and I will
send you the archive.

Thanks,
Alex

-- 
+-- Alex Wingrove / awingrove@thenet.co.uk --+

[      www.thenet.co.uk/~awingrove/blitz/       ]
[ Blitz Program Collection  and  Blitz List FAQ ]



@ENDNODE
