Subject: Triple Buffering
To: "Paul Morris" <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
In-Reply-To: <yam7284.986.3185048@post.demon.co.uk>
Message-ID: <931.285T2613T11946187@stmail.staffs.ac.uk>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-type: text/plain; charset=us-ascii
Content-transfer-encoding: 7bit
X-Mailer: THOR 2.5a (Amiga;TCP/IP)

I'd never even thought about triple buffering before!

I've converting my Flying TeleTubbies program and it runs faster than ever!

I'd been having trouble dropping frames when some big tubbies came along but
the time I used to waste in the VWait has come in handy,

I found that I needed some extra lines of code to those indicated on the list

My Set int looks liek this

SetInt 5
  DisplayBitMap 0,visible,100,100
  displaying.q=visible
End SetInt

and just before I unqueue my bitmaps I need this

  While displaying=working
  End While

  Use BitMap working
  UnQueue working

As when some small bobs come along I can fill all 3 buffers and my code
sometimes overwrote the visible buffer.

I might even upgrade it to quadruple buffering to save this wasted time =)

Amiga make's it possible
