Subject: Useful Programming Aids
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

Hi everyone,

I've been reading the thread about Visual Blitz,
and also saw the message about the RKMs being
available in AmgaGuide format,and I thought it'd
be good to have a list of other useful stuff.

So here is that little list of other useful stuff
(including alternatives to BlitzGUIGen) ...

GadToolsBox - for creating Gadtools interfaces (never!)
BlitzGUIGen - A converter for GadToolsBox interfaces
GUI2BB2 - Another GadToolsBox Converter
gtboxconv - Another GTB converter
GUIToolKit - Another one! But not really ready yet

StackSnoop - handy stack usage indicator : run your 
             program,update StackSnoop's list,and use
             your program to see its stack usage

MemMinister - shows your program's memory usage : run
              MemMinister,click on "Snapped",run your
              program,and it'll show how much memory gets
              used and how much was returned when you quit
              your program

Top - part of the Executive package,this shows your program's
      CPU usage,handy for spotting those nasty busy-loops!

RAMUsed - I think this is what it's called.It's the same as
          MemMinister,basically

Stripper - came from someone on this list.Shows all the commands
           you have available in your copy of Blitz

MonIDCMP - outputs to a CLI or file,to show every IDCMP message
           received by a window you pick

Anybody got any other cool stuff to add?

PS To Tim Johnson - a Merry Christmas to U :) 
                      Note the Lack of punctiutaion ;)
--                             ^
James L Boyd

jamesboyd@velvety.demon.co.uk

"The bigger they are,the harder they hit you..."



