X-Mailer: YAM 1.3.4 - Amiga Mailer by Marcel Beck
Subject: Version $tring
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

Hi everyone,

I just wanted to pass along a bit of information in case anyone else is having
the same problem I did.  The problem was that when I used the "Version"
command from the shell, or the "VersionWB" program on some of my execs, I was
getting the wrong results.

This turned out to be due to some of my Blitz-libraries having a version
string of their own, which was being read instead of my own version string.

The cure is to load up these libraries in a hex-editor and change the version
string  (I just changed the "$VER" to "VVER")

The libs on my system that needed this treatment were:

BD-GFX.lib
RIFX.lib
RIGFX.lib
RIZoneJoy.lib

Hope you all had a nice Christmas!
-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



@ENDNODE
