Subject: Re: Version $tring
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain


Hi Anton,

On 29-Dec-97, Anton Reinauer wrote:
>On 29-Dec-97, Curt Esser wrote:
> 
>>This turned out to be due to some of my Blitz-libraries having a
>version
>>string of their own, which was being read instead of my own version
>>string.
>  
>   What, er, version of Blitz are these from? Are you having the problem
>with Blitz 2.1 ?

Yes, the problem was with Blitz 2.1  But some of the libs came from other
places too.  If you are having the same problem, just check your "OtherLibs"
directory with the "Version" command or VersionWB and if any of them show a
version string, then these will cause the problem.

It took a while to find this, since it only will happen if your program uses
one of these libraries.  So some programs will have this problem, and some
not!

On my system I found only the 4 libraries I mentioned had version strings.
I changed them all and re-made the deflibs and now all is OK. 

>-- 
>      Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
>      


-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com




@ENDNODE
