On 11 Dec 97 at 15:53, Budda/Progress spewed forth:

> > Strangely enough, it's almost identical to the output from
> > BlitzGUIGen :/
> 
> What is BlitzGUIGen?  Is it just a program to draw the GUI and then 
> import the created source code into a Blitz2 Program?

BlitzGUIGen is a converter for the files that are created by 
GadToolsBox, which is like a paint program but creates GUIs.

BlitzGuiGen can be found on aminet at dev/basic/BlitzGUIGen18.lha
GadToolsBox can be found on aminet at dev/gui/gadtoolsbox20c.lha

Farewell, for now,

