Hi Mike,

On 01-Dec-97, Mike Carter wrote:

>Visual Blitz would go way further than GadToolsBox.  All that does is 
>let you draw the layout of thw window.  Visual Blitz would let you 
>add code to each gadget and create the source code for you all 
>in one.

Ahh, finally I understand.  I think this would be a great idea, and a good way
for beginners to get started.  And also good for people who do know how to
program, but would rather get the basic idea knocked out quickly, and then go
back and add the other stuff themselves.

>My mate and me started work on it over the weekend.  When something 
>'visual' happens we'll let everybody know on the list.  I got a book 
>out from the library about Visual Basic on the weekend too as I can't 
>actually use VB very well!

I agree with Chris  - forget the book!   Why make a copy of Visual Basic? 
Instead, make something better - easier to use and understand, and with better
features.  That's the Amiga way...

-- 
                                            Yours electronically,
                                            Curt Esser
                                            camge@ix.netcom.com



