Subject: WB Stuff
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain


hiya!

Does anyone know how to get WBDepth, Chip and Fast RAM, through OS commands?
I've been trying it with things like FastFree(), ChipFree(), WBDepth(), but
they're not very good when it comes down to Graphics card. Can anyone tell me
how to do it properly? I had the same problem with WBWidth and WBHeight, but
someone suggested I did:

cr.l=Addr Screen(0)
pubscr.l=Peek.l(scr)
NPrint Peek.w(pubscr+12),"x",Peek.w(pubscr+14)

And it works! Any ideas for the Depth, Fast Free and Chip Free?

-- 

=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=
| Alvaro Thompson - http://homepages.enterprise.net/alvaro/
=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=
| A1200T, '030, 10MB, 1.74Gb, M1438S, Canon BJC-4200, Dynalink 33.6K
=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=

