On 05-Dec-97, Alvaro Thompson wrote:

>hiya!

>Does anyone know how to get WBDepth, Chip and Fast RAM, through OS comma=
nds?
>I've been trying it with things like FastFree(), ChipFree(), WBDepth(), =
but
>they're not very good when it comes down to Graphics card. Can anyone te=
ll me
>how to do it properly? I had the same problem with WBWidth and WBHeight,=
 but
>someone suggested I did:

>cr.l=3DAddr Screen(0)
>pubscr.l=3DPeek.l(scr)
>NPrint Peek.w(pubscr+12),"x",Peek.w(pubscr+14)

>And it works! Any ideas for the Depth, Fast Free and Chip Free?

Well depth you should get from the bitmap.

screensbitmap 0,0; Screen 0 bitmap -> bitmap object 0
bmap.l=3Daddr bitmap(0)
depth.b=3Dpeek.b(bmap+5); and the depth of bitmap is here.

And the available memory is get like this.
First here is all the memory flags!

Mem typeBit numberInfo

#PUBLIC0Shared memory (HAVE to be in physical mem)
Set this only, if you realy need it!!!!!
#CHIP1Chip mem
#FAST2Fast mem
#LOCAL8Reset proof mem
#24BITDMA9This mem is in DMA area
#KICK10Kick tagable memory
#CLEAR16In allocmem Clear the reserved mem
#LARGEST17Largest block! (avoid in allocmem)
#REVERSE18In allocmem Start from the highest address
#TOTAL19Total amount of memory
#NO_EXPUNGE31If alloc fails. don't expunge unused
libraries or devices.


chip.l=3Davailmem_(2^#CHIP)
fast.l=3Davailmem_(2^#FAST)
all.l=3Davailmem_(2^#TOTAL)

