Subject: What I want for Xmas
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

Dear Santa,
   I would *really* like the following things this xmas:

   (1) A Blitz basic with a professional integrated environment that
       has all the mod cons at the click of a gadget. Oh and make the
       compiler independant please, just in case the source editor is
       crap...

   (2) A fast bitmap scale routine so I can continue coding my RPG 
       project. 

   (3) Someone to explain why I should use SETINT for double-buffering
       and not VWAIT.

   (4) Someone to explain the fastest way to handle shape collision. 

   (5) One of those new miggys I saw in FORMAT the other day.

   (6) Oh and Joanne Guest. Ive been begging you years for this one.
       I wake up on christmas day every year all excited and all I 
       find in my bed is the missus... ;)
       

Cheers,      
MICHAEL.
--|---------------------------------------------------------------------
  &  Michael Smith (mrsmith@hangman.demon.co.uk)                        
