Subject: Window Bitmap
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=us-ascii
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Hi  everyone

  You know `BitmaptoWindow` , does anyone know how to do the opposite
  of that.
  I want to grab a windows bitmap to use as a bitmap, preferably without
  the windows borders , just the graphics inside the window.
  I know I will have to find the address of the windows bitmap from
  the windows structure but when I was looking at this structure I
  found, addresses to rastports and Layers . Each had a bitmap
  pointer and also I found a super bitmap pointer.
  Which is the one I need ? And will I need the others sometimes as
  well ?
  The reason I want to do this is because I want to use the datatype
  lib to load pictures and that only lets me use the datatype on a
  window not a bitmap. So I want to use it in the normal way and then
  transfer the graphic to a bitmap.
   Does anyone know a better way to use datatypes on a bitmap ?
   
 
Thanks for any comments

DAVE


@ENDNODE
