Hi,



>I have a window with a pile of gadtools gadgets attached to it.  When=20
>I clear the window (for a reason) I want to redraw all the gadgets on=20
>it.  Is it possible to do this without a FOR ... NEXT loop and Redraw=20
>each gadget.  Is there a possible Intuition function.  I've tried=20
>GT_RefreshWindow but can't get it working.  I might be doing=20
>something wrong though.

GT_RefreshWindow is generally only used after opening a window

Try this instead -

*glist.Gadget =3D Peek.l(Addr GTList(0))
*win.Window =3D Peek.l(Addr Window(0))

RefreshGList_ *glist, *win, 0, -1

Ciao
Julian Kinraid




@ENDNODE
