> 
> I was wondering, is there anything like that on the Amiga atm? If so, what is
> it, and where can I get it?
> 
I did this a few years ago as part of a system known as "Enclock".  
It was a nice hard drive security program which gave each user their 
own 'startup-sequence' and ENV: directory.  It also had features to 
secure the machine whilst you went to the toilet and a 
log-off/re-boot.  This was back in my AMOS days and it still looked 
quite nice (even if I do say so mayself).  Some people may remember 
it (please?) as it scord quite nicely in most Amiga magazines.  It 
was last featured on CUCD #7.  I've since then started to re-code it 
for version 4 in Blitz Basic but got side-tracked with other projects 
(you know how it is!).

Anyway - there you go.

Cheerio,

Mike.
