On 03-Dec-97, Alvaro Thompson wrote:

>Hiya ppl.

Hi there :-)

>Me and a friend might start a program called MultiBench soon. It's basically
a
>util that lets you have Multiple Logins to Workbench (Or DOpus, or any other
>OS proggy u may use) like on Windows '95. 

>I was wondering, is there anything like that on the Amiga atm? If so, what is
>it and where can I get it?

There was one called something like MultiUserFileSystem or something, it
replaced the HardDrives file system with a custom one, meaning the
hard drive could only be accessed when the correct password was
entered.  It allowed multiple users with different accounts, meaning they
could only access certain areas that you configured.  There was also
local mail as well so you could send messages to each account to 
another.  Its on Aminet somewhere.. Hope that helps :-)

Byyyee!,

David Hodge/Electrus Software



