 Hello,

>I still haven't got the RIListView! Wasn't is supposed to  come
>with BSS (if it did, I didn't get it) ?

Hmm never heard of it. I think you mean the RICallHook  library,
and I dont think it came with the BBS.

>Does this  library  let  you  use  colours/styles  as  well  as
>multiple selection/etc in listviews?

I havn't tried it myself, only looked at the example source  for
it, and it showed how to used colors in the list view, aswell as
including shapes in the listview gadget.

>Does anyone know where I can get it? Coz I need it *NOW* !! :)

I think someone from the list can send it to you. I dont have my
copy  anymore,  since  I  didn't need it, and includingdont like
having librarys that I dont need, since they take up a free  lib
num.

>Y'know those menu's in most MUI programs  that  look  like  the
>menu at the top of the screen? Anyone know how I co do that? As
>far as I know, a window isn't used. Hmm...

Hmm I'm not  sure  what  you  mean  with  this.  ALL  menus  are
"connected"  to a window or a screen. And in MUI's case they are
connected to the MUI window (NOTE that this isn't a "normal"  wb
window). With the new version of the EFMUILib you can attach
gt menus to your MUI windows.

>Is there a helpguide or something available for  EFMUILib  ?  I
>can't  for  the  life  of me, see how to open a standard window
>with 2 listviews in them!! Why are  there  loads  of  different
>(and  seemingly  random-ish)  ID  numbers? Using GadTools is so
>much easier, but I can't seem to do  multiple  selection  using
>GadTools ListViews. :(

I cant see what you find hard to use with the  EFMUILib.  Is  it
all  the  constants (tags), you have to use? You can find all of
them in the MUI developer autodocs (mui38dev.lha in  dev/mui  on
aminet). And  what  do  you  mean  with "loads  of  diffrent  ID
numbers"? Of  course  you  need  to  give each gaget it's own ID
number, how else whould you  check if the gadget has been alterd
in anyway?

We tired to make the EFMUILib as easy as possible, and as far as
I  can  see,  people in general find it easy to use. The lib has
become a big hit. If you have any questions on how to do  things
with  the  EFMUILib,  then please e-mail me or Erwan Fouret. Our
e-mail addreses are in the EFMUILib Guide. But keep in mind that
we WONT write the WHOLE application GUI code, only help you with
parts that you cant make work.

And please dont send 500lines of code and ask us to find the bug
that  makes the MUI stuff crash, since we will only ignore those
kind of requests. Please try to hunt down where the bug is,  and
then ask us to sort it out. We are constantly impoving the usage
of the lib, aswell as adding new commands.

As you seem "new" to this list, and  has  proberbly  missed  the
discussion  about  the  EFMUIlib  questions,  I will tell you it
again. DONT send any questions about the EFMUILib to this mailing
list, because the lib is so new that people most likely dont know
how to solve them, since they havn't tried it them self. Please
send the questions to me (Andreas H=E5kansson) or to Erwan Fouret.

We are the founders of Vivid Imagination and also  the  authours
of  the EFMUILib, and we should be able to help you with most of
your questions. Please note that it can take a few days or  even
a  week  or two, since we get these kind of mails every day, but
we will look at your mail asson as we get the time.

And regarding your question on how to open a MUI window with two
listviews in them. I can write a small exmaple on how to do this
if you want. Please e-mail me directly and tell me how you  want
it  to  be.  Please  not that the MUI listviews are able to have
many columns of data in them.

 ByE!

-- =

