	id OAA09197 for <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>;
	Sat, 6 Dec 1997 14:43:07 GMT
From: Paul Anderton <paul@ebabes.mersinet.co.uk>
To: Mail <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Sat, 06 Dec 1997 14:23:27 +0500
Message-ID: <yam7279.1362.3419528@mail.mersinet.co.uk>
X-Mailer: YAM 1.3.3a - Amiga Mailer by Marcel Beck
Subject: [Blitz] Registration & Tooltypes
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain

Hi Guys and Guyesses!

Chapter 1 - I have in my hand a piece of paper...

I`ve been noticing a lot of stuff about the UK blitz distributors.
Guildhall leisure aren't able to help, and Red when Excited seem
to have taken over...

The thing is, where does this leave me and my registration card?

I want to register, I need to register, I HAVE to register, but what
happens if I send it to Guildhall Leisure and they consign it to the
round file(!)? Should I send it to RWE? Where are RWE?
What's going on? Who am I?

Chapter 2 - Take a letter, Miss Tool...

I was wondering about tooltypes. Is there an EASY way to send
parameters via tooltypes to my program? I tried (but I failed) to
use that parameter thingy (I've been off the Mig for a couple of
weeks - you should see my mail folder. The other man-made object
visible from space!), and if I can't use tooltypes, I'll have to use a
prefs file, which would be a bit excessive, as the program is quite
small!


Any help with either of these would be appreciated muchly @:-)=

TTFN

Paul "E" Babes

-- 
You have been reading...
paul@ebabes.mersinet.co.uk

"I Think therefore I am"
                                    French philosophy

"All that can be thought is not true"
                                    Hindu philosophy



@ENDNODE
