> On 06-Dec-97, Paul Anderton wrote:
> >Hi Guys and Guyesses!

> >I was wondering about tooltypes. Is there an EASY way to send
> >parameters via tooltypes to my program? I tried (but I failed) to
> >use that parameter thingy (I've been off the Mig for a couple of
> >weeks - you should see my mail folder. The other man-made object
> >visible from space!), and if I can't use tooltypes, I'll have to use a
> >prefs file, which would be a bit excessive, as the program is quite
> >small!

Get a copy of "AaronsIconLib" - if you haven't got it,mail me
and I'll send the .obj file and docs.

I've also written a little program to test the library,so I can
send that too,if you want it...

Curt Esser (hi,Curt) mentioned the RIToolTypesLib.That's something
I just made use of tonight! It's a little more awkward,but it can write
tooltype info back out,which AaronsIconLib can't do.So it depends
if you need to put stuff back out or not.

Mail me if you want some more info...

-- 
James L Boyd

jamesboyd@velvety.demon.co.uk

"The bigger they are,the harder they hit you..."



